title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have raisins soak in warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk to eggs and cooled melted butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour.

title: salem clam chowder
directions: Put potatoes and onions in a 4-quart soup pot.
Add water to cover and a shake of salt and pepper (at least 1/2 teaspoon pepper).
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes until potatoes and onions are cooked.
Add minced clams and chowder, stirring well over medium or low heat.
Add both milks.
Again, season to taste. Bring just to a boil and simmer at least 15 minutes.
Add butter. Do not let boil.
Can be done a day before.
Yield:

title: cream pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven!
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, whipping after each egg.
Add heavy cream and flour, adding small amounts of cream at a time.
Mix well.
Spoon in stem (Bundt) cake pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325°. Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Hull, wash and quarter berries and add together with nut meats to butter-sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

Line bottom of refrigerator dish with broken vanilla wafers, then add layer of strawberry mixture. Continue alternating layers until all ingredients are used, finishing with a layer of wafers on top. Cover dish and place in refrigerator to chill at least 12 hours.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger in pan and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.

title: poor folks singles
directions: Melt butter over slow heat.
Add milk and flour.
Cook until desired thickness (add more milk if needed).
Add hamburger or dry beef, bring to slow boil, then pour over toasted bread.

title: light angel food dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake in half to make two layers.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread pudding mixture on top of bottom layer.
Replace top layer.
Serve with more Cool Whip and fresh strawberries.

title: grama's cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into a large bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg and juice at once. Stir until evenly moistened.
Fold in raisins, nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or mixer.
Put in a large buttered pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad #2
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os and put in refrigerator until creamy. Add Cool Whip. Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise; add pineapple and other ingredients.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Roll mixture into 1-inch ball and set aside.
Combine chocolate morsels and paraffin in top of a double boiler and place over hot water, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Place several peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture; roll with spoon to coat.
Remove from mixture with spoons and place on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pizza
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage.
Add seasonings.
Add cheese and melt together.
Spread on party rye.
Place in freezer bags. Freeze.
When ready to eat, place in 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix chunks of pineapple, sugar and flour and spread in ungreased baking dish.
Mix cheese, crackers, butter and pineapple juice and spread on top of pineapple chunk mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: easy to make biscuits
directions: Sift 2 cups Bisquick mix into mixing bowl.
Pour in the 1/2 pint of whipping cream.
Stir until blended.
Flour bar or use wax paper to pour mixture of dough on.
I use flour on bar.
Sift or dust flour on dough to prevent sticking to hands.
Also this makes the dough very manageable while forming into biscuits.
Use Pam to spray flat cookie sheet with a good coating or use shortening. Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°, then maybe 2 minutes or broil to a good brown.

title: mom's apple cake(breakfast)
directions: In small mixer bowl cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Then add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Then add water and beat well.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add butter.
Add eggs and vanilla, then pecans and chocolate chips. Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set, at 325°.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients, except dressing; pour in dish.
Top with dressing and dot with additional margarine; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: lime cucumber pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers and put them in the lime solution for 24 hours. Stir once in awhile. Take out and rinse well.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed. Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put water and milk in a bowl.
Add sugar to milk mixture.
If sugar won't dissolve, set bowl in warm water and stir until dissolved.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together, heat until sugar is dissolved. Let cool.
Drain all vegetables and mix all of them together. Pour oil, sugar and vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Toss thoroughly.
Chill overnight and serve.
You can drain before serving or leave as is.
I leave as is and serve with slotted spoon.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; allow to cool.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Alternately add dry ingredients with buttermilk to butter-sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites; fold into mixture.
Turn oven on to 350°.
Prepare four 9-inch round pans by spraying with a nonstick baking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.
After done, allow layers to cool completely before frosting.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Place beans and 2 tablespoons water in 1-quart casserole; cover.
Microwave at High 4 to 7 minutes or until beans are tender, stirring to break apart after half the time.
Drain. Cover and set aside.

title: potato pancakes(latkahs)
directions: Grate potatoes into bowl.
Drain liquid and grate in the onion.
Add eggs and seasonings.
Mix in dry ingredients until batter is smooth but heavy . Using a large frying pan, drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry on both sides until golden brown. Remove and drain on paper towels and keep hot in warm oven.
Serve with sour cream, cottage cheese and/or applesauce.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Immediately stir in chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in rice, chicken, mushrooms, green pepper, pimiento and almonds.
Pour into a greased baking dish, 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 12 servings (3-inch square per portion).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Cream them.
Put in a casserole. Using a spoon, hollow out hole in center.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Put in hole in potatoes.
Cover top with cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix coarse fresh bread crumbs, grated Parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon olive oil and minced garlic in a medium bowl.
Slice about 1/3-inch off tops of ripe tomatoes; place, cut sides up, in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle tomatoes with crumb mixture and drizzle with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until crumbs are toasted.
Yield: 5 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix together in a 13-quart mixing bowl.
Toast in oven at 275° until golden brown.
When cold, mix with Grape-Nuts.
Add chocolate chips or butterscotch and raisins, if you wish.

title: calico baked beans
directions: *1 lb. is approximately. weight of these cans.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of batter in greased skillet.
Add cheese.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 400° to 450° until done.

title: hot peppers(canning)
directions: Place all ingredients in jars (sterilized).
Cut up peppers into bite size pieces.
Put peppers into spice filled jars.
Press down hard with wooden spoon. Fill to 1/2-inch of top.
Boil 1 quart of vinegar and 1 quart of water.
When it comes to a rolling boil, pour into jars and cover peppers.
Clean top of jars and put on sterilized lids.
Ready in 2 weeks.
For quarts, double spices.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and shake well.
Pour over freshly cooked, drained asparagus while hot and let stand at room temperature 15 minutes.
Add oil; toss lightly taking care not to break asparagus; let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes longer, then chill until serving time.
Drain and serve on a bed of lettuce garnished with hard cooked egg and other garnishes as desired (such as tomato wedges, capers, sprigs of fresh parsley).

title: hawaiian ham sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread evenly on slices of bread.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In medium saucepan combine broth and rice.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until tender. Stir in onions and carrot during last 5 minutes of cooking. Combine cream or milk, flour and pepper.
Stir into rice mixture. Cook and stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
If desired, stir in sherry.
Garnish with parsley or chives.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flours, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a separate bowl, whisk together milk and eggs.
Pour milk mixture into flour mixture and stir until relatively lump free.
Whisk in melted butter, then add apples. Spoon onto hot griddle.
Serve with Spiced Cider Sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Slowly add flour, then vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky mountain brisket with barbecue sauce(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine salt, pepper, chili powder and bay leaves.
Rub meat completely with liquid smoke.
Place meat, fat side up, in a large roasting pan.
Sprinkle dry seasoning mixture on top.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 4 hours at 325°.
Scrape seasoning off meat and cut in very thin slices across the grain.
Serve with Barbecue Sauce.

title: grilled cornish hens
directions: Wash Cornish hens and place in a pan.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over hens.
Let stand for at least 1 hour. Drain and reserve marinade.
Pull neck skin back and secure wings against body.
Tie wings and legs together.
Follow manufacturer's directions for securing hens on spit, then start the motor.
Grill for 1 hour or until golden brown and done, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine pie plant with sugar and flour; turn into pie shell. Dot with butter.
Cover top with crust, allowing steam vents and bake in hot 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Lessen heat and bake until well browned.
Top with 1/2 cup strawberries, 1/2 cup apples or 1/2 cup peaches.

title: french custard pe
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: grandpa's famous meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, celery, onion, peppers and bread crumbs thoroughly with hands until bread is no longer visible.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour tomato sauce over the top. Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese potato souffle'
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, mix mashed potatoes, oleo and cheese until melted.
Add milk and salt.
Fold in eggs.
Put mixture in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts on top.
Bake at 325° in glass pan only about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick turkey schnitzel
directions: Rinse cutlets and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper or Adolph's seasoning.
Blend egg, water and Dijon mustard on plate. Put bread crumbs on another plate.
Dip cutlets in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet. Heat oil on medium heat until hot.
Fry cutlets one minute on each side until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash; parboil for 5 minutes.
Combine beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 of sauce.
Pile mixture into peppers in large baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over each pepper.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: narsai's chocolate decadence cake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Reserve 1 section of chocolate for cake decoration.
In heavy saucepan on low heat, melt broken chocolate with butter, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
In top of double boiler, beat eggs with sugar until mixture is lukewarm and sugar is dissolved.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove from heat and beat until quadrupled and very thick.
Blend flour into egg mixture; fold into chocolate mixture, a little at a time.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Blend butter, pecans and vanilla.
Add flour and sugar.
Shape into small fingers.
Bake at 325° to 350° until lightly browned. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients into medium size pot.
Cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes.

title: hoecake
directions: Griddle should be well greased and very hot.
Pour into 3 tablespoons of batter in griddle.
Fry until brown on one side. Edges should be lacy.
Turn, brown on other side.
Serve hot.

title: eight-layer salad
directions: Heat potatoes and 3 cups of water to boiling in 2 1/2-quart saucepan; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse under running cold water; drain.
Mix 1 cup of water and the sauce mix in saucepan; heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring.
Cool.
Stir in dressing and sour cream. Mix sauce mixture and potatoes.
Layer lettuce, carrots, celery, onion, peas, potato mixture, cheese and bacon in a 3 or 3 1/2-quart clear bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve with additional Thousand Island dressing.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine morsels, margarine and corn syrup over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill. Store in refrigerator.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: upside-down fudge cake
directions: Spread coconut and nuts into bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour mixture over coconut and nuts. Mix margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: orange julius
directions: Add orange juice, sugar, water, vanilla and milk in blender, then add ice cubes a handful at a time.
Blend, then add the rest of the ice cubes slowly.
After all ice cubes are blended in, serve right away.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball (crackling stage).
Add butter and peanuts.
Then cook until golden brown.
Remove from fire, add vanilla and baking soda, then stir thoroughly and pour into buttered cookie sheet.
When hardened, break into pieces.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool upright in pop bottle.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce, red pepper, celery and peas in layers.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; warm 20 seconds in microwave.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then cover with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top before serving.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: Remove corn kernels with sharp knife into saucepan.
Stir in water.
Cover and steam for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove cover and cook for 2 minutes more.
Combine drained corn, peppers, onions and cilantro in bowl.
In another bowl, whisk olive oil, lime juice, orange juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over corn mixture.
Toss and chill covered for at least 2 hours.

title: blender coconut pie(no crust to bake)
directions: Put into the blender and turn to high.
Count to ten slowly as you blend.
Spray or grease pie pan and bake at 350° until light brown.
It is good served warm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients.
Let simmer over low-medium heat.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, vanilla and milk until blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Mound and freeze 2 to 3 hours.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: "no fail" 7 minute frosting
directions: Cook in double boiler.
Beat with a mixer all the time frosting is cooking.
Put all ingredients in top of double boiler and mix some before you put over boiling water to cook.
(You may keep the vanilla out until you remove from cooking.)
Cook approximately seven minutes or until the frosting holds a peak on beaters or in pan.
Remove from heat and continue to beat approximately one minute.
Add vanilla if haven't before.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine
all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl; stir well.
Pour
half
of mixture into a greased 10-inch iron skillet; top
with
cheese.
Add
remaining mixture;
bake at 450° for 30 minutes, or until done.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: balloon creatures
directions: Stirring, mix plaster until creamy.
Pour into an empty balloon, using funnel.
Set plaster filled balloon on table and hold until firm.
Let go and allow to dry at least 1/2 hour. Tear off balloon.
Decorate and paint as animals, creatures or wonderful designs of unknown origin.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients together in mixing bowl or blender.
Mix until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until time to serve.
Pour into punch cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pork chop-potato bake
directions: Cook pork chops in frying pan for 15 minutes in oil or Pam. Combine soup and milk; pour over hash brown potatoes in casserole dish.
Top with pork chops, then fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crayfish dip
directions: Soften Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise, ketchup, hot sauce and onion.
Mix together well.
Add crayfish pieces and mix again.
Serve as dip with chips or spread on crackers.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and meat.
Blend flour into meat mixture. Add chili powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in corn and tomatoes.
Pour into casserole; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Prepare 1/2 package cornbread mix according to directions on box.
Spoon over casserole, then bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach-feta phyllo pie(greek croustade)
directions: Defrost the spinach in microwave.
Mash the Feta and cottage cheese together.
Drain and squeeze the frozen spinach.
Add spinach to cheese.
Mix.

title: open faced broiler buns
directions: Grind together
all
ingredients, except rolls.
Spread evenly on hamburg rolls.
Place under broiler until bubbly and brown. Serves 10.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichoke hearts in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in uncovered casserole for 30 minutes or until slightly browned.
Serve hot with chunks of French bread or crackers for dipping.

title: trifle dessert
directions: Mix sour cream with pudding; put on bottom layer.
Add pieces of cake to next layer, then Cool Whip, then fruit.
Repeat layers; end with fruit on top.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Layer crackers in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over crackers.
Bake at 250° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy; gradually add the flour.
Add lemon extract, vanilla, eggs and 7-Up.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or insert toothpick and it comes out clean.
Cool completely before icing.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream Genesis 18 with Jeremiah 6. Beat in yolks of Isaiah 10, one at a time.
Sift together Leviticus 24, 2 Kings 2, Amos 4, Exodus 30 and 2 Chronicles 9. Blend into creamed mixture alternately with Judges 4. Beat whites of Isaiah 10 until stiff; fold in.
Fold in chopped Genesis 43, Jeremiah 24 and 2 Samuel 16. Fold in chopped Genesis 43, Jeremiah 24 and 2 Samuel 16.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and dusted with Leviticus 24.
Bake in a 325° oven 1 hour and 10 minutes, until cake is golden brown and cake tester inserted in cake comes out clean. Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serve drizzled with Burnt Sugar Syrup and decorate with whole Genesis 43.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 Tbsp. of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese and remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm about 4 hours.

title: one hundred percent whole wheat rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into 1/4 cup lukewarm milk or water; let stand 10 minutes.
Combine 1 cup scalded milk, brown sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir yeast mixture and add to lukewarm mixture.
Add whole wheat flour in two additions, mixing well after each.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead gently 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°), until double in size or when dent remains after light pressure. Knead ball with fist, folding edges to center.
Turn smooth side up in bowl; let stand 20 minutes.
Brush with melted shortening. Cover and let rise in warm place until again double in size.
Bake in hot oven, 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mash cream cheese until soft; beat in sugar, vanilla and topping.
Pour 1/2 of cream cheese mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish, then blueberry mixture.
Top with remainder of cream cheese mix. Cool in refrigerator.

title: turkey breast ala normandy
directions: Peel and core the apples.
Cut apples into 1/2-inch cubes. Place in bowl.
Add lemon juice and mix thoroughly; set aside. Sprinkle turkey slices with salt and pepper.
Dip turkey slices into flour.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet over medium heat.
When hot, add the turkey slices, a few pieces at a time; saute until lightly browned on both sides, about 4 minutes on each side.
Remove cooked turkey slices from pan and arrange them on an oven-proof platter.
Place in oven heated to 200°.
Add apples, lemon juice and Calvados to the skillet.
Stir and scrape up all the brown crusts in the skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 3 minutes.
Add cream and continue cooking until the mixture has turned to a rich, ivory color.
Reduce heat and cook uncovered, stirring frequently, until the sauce has reduced by about 1/2 and coats a spoon, about 10 minutes.
Spoon the sauce over the turkey slices and serve.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together the flour, oat bran, baking soda, baking powder and brown sugar.
Stir in apples and carrots until dry ingredients absorb moisture.
Make well in the middle of mixture.
Add eggs, milk, oil, vanills and nuts; stir.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for a 13 x 9-inch pan or 30 to 32 minutes for an 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Frost, if desired.

title: party salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Decorate top with pecan halves and cherry halves.

title: no-fuss chocolate chewy squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Spread evenly in a well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers.
Melt margarine. Add sugar.
Beat egg in milk and add to other mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat and add pecans, 1 cup cracker crumbs and coconut.
Pour over crackers in pan.
Layer another of whole crackers on top and ice.

title: iced tea
directions: Bring 2 quarts cold water just to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Put 1 cup sugar and juice of 1 lemon (strained) into 2-quart pitcher.
Add hot steeped tea.
Mix well.
Fill large glass to top with ice.
Pour on tea.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin, oil, water and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins, if desired.

title: brownie and fruit delite
directions: Layer in glass bowl.
Break up 6 brownies into bottom of bowl. Cover with Cool Whip.
Layer as follows: strawberries, 6 brownies (broken up), Cool Whip, bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecan chips.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ham nuggets
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix until a dough is formed.
Mold 2 to 3 teaspoons of dough around one-inch cube of boiled ham.
Enclose ham entirely.
Chill until firm. When ready to serve, bring to room temperature.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1 cup flour.
Put nuts and water into flour and add to rest.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°
and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve in wedges.

title: grandma june's banana bread(now known as "crossover banana bread")
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Mix very well with mixer. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon dijon chicken breast
directions: Combine breadcrumbs and lemon juice, stirring well.
Combine lemon and lime juice with mustard.
Brush mixture over both sides of chicken.
Dredge chicken in breadcrumbs.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; coat well with cooking spray. Sprinkle with remaining breadcrumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
Garnish with lemon slice.

title: crab stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until desired serving temperature is reached.
Do not boil.
Serve with crackers.

title: garden vegetable calzone
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Spray cookie sheet with non-stick cooking spray.
In medium bowl combine mushrooms, bell pepper, zucchini, and onions.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and basil; mix well.
Unroll dough; place on cookie sheet.
Roll dough into 14 inch square; cut into 4-7 inch squares.
Place 1/4 c. on 1/2 of each square, spread to within 1/ 2 in. of edge.
Top each with 1/4 of vegetable mixture.
Fold dough in half over filling; press edges firmly with fork to seal.
Brush each with beaten egg white.
With sharp knife cut 2 - 3 slits in top of each for steam to escape. Bake at 425 degrees for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with heated pizza or spaghetti sauce for dipping.

title: beef and bean chimichangas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Remove meat and set aside.
Place 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet and saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in beef, tomatoes, salsa, chili powder, coriander, thyme, salt, cayenne and cumin.
Cook over medium-low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in beans.
Place 1/2 cup of mixture in center of each tortilla.
Fold edges around beef.
May need to secure with toothpick.
Fry in 375° oil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Fry only 1 or 2 chimichangas at a time.
Remove and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with shredded cheese while hot.
Serve immediately with additional salsa.

title: traditional pizza dough
directions: Yields 2 pounds of dough.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the vanilla wafers, 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve a few crumbs for top.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon juice well.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 300° until firm on top (approximately 15 minutes).
Mix jello, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 5 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook and cool.
Add 1 quart fresh strawberries.
Pour over cooled cheese layer.
Put Cool Whip over all.
Top with crumbs.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
(Freeze cranberries and they will grind better.)

title: "lite fruit salad"
directions: Optional:
Other canned fruits may be added if desired.

title: mom schrader's country chicken
directions: Put cut up chicken in pot; cover with water.
Put lid on pot. Simmer for a half hour.

title: peanut sauce for pasta
directions: In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat peanut butter with water until smooth.
Stir in vinegar and next 4 ingredients until blended.
Add cooked and drained pasta; toss gently to coat well. Serve immediately.

title: roasted vegetable soup
directions: In large stockpot melt over medium heat the butter and olive oil, add and saut about 20 minutes the potatoes, zucchini, corn, cabbage, onion and peppers.
Add the following and simmer 30 minutes - 1 hour depending on desired tenderness: Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce vegetable broth green peas, red beans, green beans and water.
Then flavor with the bouillon cubes, garlic, red pepper, black pepper and Lawry's salt.

title: brownies
directions: This recipe can be frozen and eaten as needed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream of shrimp soup and cream cheese together.
Add frozen popcorn shrimp to taste.
Stir in the Worcestershire sauce. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut in small pieces.
Drain vegetables; dilute chicken soup with 1/2 can of water.
Prepare stuffing with 1 cup water and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine, using "in-the-bird" directions.
In a 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole layer as follows:
1/2 stuffing, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 soup and 1/2 vegetable.
Repeat layers, ending with stuffing on top.

title: puff pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Beat eggs slightly. Mix in milk, then flour and nutmeg. Leave batter slightly lumpy. Melt butter in large skillet with ovenproof handle. Pour batter in skillet. Bake 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with lemon juice and then sifted confectioner's sugar. Pancake will puff while baking and fall when removed from oven. Serves 2 people as main breakfast entre and 4 people as side breakfast entre.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in half of the dry ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Mix in milk and rest of dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets; bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cookies should be placed about 2 inches apart.
Frost, if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine dressing with mayonnaise and sugar to taste.
Break up broccoli and cauliflower into serving size pieces.
Toss vegetables with cheese and bacon.
Serve with dressing.

title: ranch tortillas(appetizer)
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, Ranch dressing and chopped green onions together in small bowl.
Spread evenly on tortillas. Sprinkle remaining ingredients evenly over tortillas.
(Don't overdo.)
Roll tortillas and place seam side down on plate. Refrigerate a minimum of 2 hours.
Take knife and slice crosswise about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange on serving plate. These are guaranteed to disappear quickly!

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Fold in walnuts and cherries.
Drop cookies on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until done.

title: oven baked salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Flake, removing skin and large bones.
Process bread into fine crumbs.
Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl. Shape into 8 patties, pressing together firmly.
Bake on a lightly oiled cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes on each side.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stuff into red or green bell peppers that have been cut lengthwise and cleaned.
Place into a greased, shallow baking dish.
Cover each pepper with 1 teaspoon of ketchup.
Pour 1/2 cup water into bottom of baking dish. Cover and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sawdust
directions: Make jello.
Add marshmallows and chill to set.
Cook over medium heat the sugar, flour and pineapple juice until thick. Allow to cool, then spread over jello and top with Cool Whip, cheese and coconut.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add pecans.
Press into 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place bell pepper, onion, celery, garlic and Tabasco sauce in blender and chop; set aside.
Cream together the sugar, cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Now, combine creamed mixture and chopped vegetables.
Add chopped or blended shrimp; mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: snicker pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spoon in 8-inch pie pan (glass); freeze. Serve frozen.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Boil meat in water until it falls apart, approximately 3 hours.
Shred and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cooked spaghetti into pan.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over spaghetti. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Brown hamburger; pour over noodles.
Add oregano and pizza sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use care in selecting.
Do not choose too young and only of a variety reared in a good moral atmosphere.
Once decided upon and selected, let that part remain forever settled.
Give your entire thought to preparing for home use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water.

Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing with patience, sweetened with smiles, flavored with kisses to taste, wrapped well in a mantle, baked with a steady fire of devotion and served with honey, peaches and cream.
Thus prepared they will keep for years.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Wash blueberries and drain.
Put muffin mix, egg and water in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Stir with fork until blended.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle blueberries, brown sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Use fork to fold into batter to create a marbled effect. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Use knife to loosen sides.
I put a few tablespoons of icing from a can on top of it.
After it melts, spread around.

title: vegetarian lasagne (heart healthy)
directions: Be creative.
Add chopped zucchini, squash, eggplant, etc.

title: potato vegetable medley
directions: In a greased 1-quart baking dish combine carrots, onion, broth and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and remaining seasoned salt.	Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until veggies are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: london tea cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Take 2/3 of dough and roll 1/4-inch thick in greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top of dough.
Roll out remaining 1/3 of dough.
Cut in strips with pastry wheel, crisscross on filling.
Brush with one egg yolk and small amount of milk beaten together.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple spice cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, salt and cloves.
Add applesauce, yogurt, eggs and oil; blend well, using a spoon.
Stir in raisins. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and add carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 325° for 20 minutes.
Great to take to a picnic!

title: potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm potatoes; chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onions and chopped egg whites.
Sieve yolks; mix with the mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard; fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours.
(I usually chill longer.) Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all together, kneading well.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Make your rolls.
Let rise before baking at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: window panes
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add chocolate chips; cool and pour into large bowl.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Put on waxed paper and shape into 3 or 4 logs approximately 12-inches long each. Chill 2 hours; slice to serve.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Fry onions and peppers in Crisco for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Remove the pan and add meat, seasoning and eggs.
Mix well. Put into baking dish half the corn, half meat mixture, then half the tomatoes.
Repeat and cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook at 375° in oven for 1/2 hour.

title: black midnight devil's food
directions: Combine cocoa and hot water.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add to creamed shortening, sugar and eggs alternately with dry ingredients, sifted together.
Bake in two round 8-inch layers (1 inch thick) or an 8-inch square (1 1/2 inches thick) pan.
Bake at 350° 30 to 35 minutes for layer or 45 to 55 minutes for square.

title: almond rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in rice, mushrooms, seasoning and green onions. Cook and
stir
over
medium
heat	for about 10 minutes or until tender.
Spoon
into
greased shallow 2 quart casserole. Cover and chill
until
ready to bake.
(This part can be done a day ahead.) Heat oven to 325°. Stir in broth and almonds. Cover and bake for
1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey in a brown paper bag
directions: Dry cavity; rub it with salt.
Butter inside and out.
Shake stuffing into the cavity.
Never pack it in.
Truss, tying legs together firmly, pulling wings up over the breast and tying all close to body.
Rub butter into every pore of the bird that you may have missed, extra coating to the breast.

title: spaghetti sauce italiano
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and sausage; drain off fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, Burgundy, olives, bay leaves, garlic, Worcestershire, sugar, chili powder, salt and pepper.
If too thick for your preference, add 1/3 cup water.
Simmer until ready to eat.
Blend water slowly into cornstarch; stir into tomato mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over spaghetti; pass the Parmesan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until combined.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Pour in nuts. Gently fold in carrots.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Don't overbake.
Cool in pans on racks 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely, then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: almond pine cones
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add bacon, onion, dill and pepper; mix well.
Chill and form one pine cone or two small ones on a serving platter.
Beginning at narrow end, press almonds at a slight angle into cheese mixture in rows.
Continue overlapping rows until all the cheese is covered.
Garnish with artificial pine sprigs.
Serve with crackers.

title: hawaiian spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except spareribs.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Cover spareribs; bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornbread.
Mix mayonnaise and juice well. Crumble cornbread and layer it and mixture with the mayonnaise and juice.
Repeat.
Cool 2 hours before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Scald skins off and mash tomatoes to give the juice in which to cook the rest of the ingredients for no water is added.
Cook 1 hour and put in glass jars and seal tight.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Cut pocket in each pita.
Fill each pocket with 3 tablespoons spaghetti sauce, cheese, mushrooms, pepperoni and sausage.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: jimbo's favorite baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and bell pepper until meat is done.
Mix beans, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar together; mix well.
Drain burger mixture and add to bean mixture. Mix well.
Cook in microwave oven for 15 minutes or in regular oven until hot and bubbly.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown hamburger and drain oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes or longer.

title: angel puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except powdered sugar) together; roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet, bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool; roll in powdered sugar.

title: mountain mama mud slide
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute bacon or butter and onion in kettle.
Add fish, potatoes, corn and water.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Just before serving, add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Serve.

title: texas hot
directions: Grind all peppers in blender.
Add tomatoes and blend again. Add jalapenos, onion, celery seed, mustard seed, vinegar, pickling salt and dill and cook 30 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.
May be processed in hot water bath, if desired.
Makes 2 pints.

title: southern style potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in large pan.
Pour melted stick of oleo over and mix. Separately, combine sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, cheese and soup. Mix this with potatoes.
Pour into shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: fruit punch
directions: Crush bananas in blender.
In large container mix pineapple juice, lemonade, orange juice, bananas and water.
Freeze until slush.
Add 3 quarts 7-Up or Sprite.
Make 1 large punch bowl.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top; do not stir.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mozzarella tamale
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in a nonstick skillet or Dutch oven, stirring, until beef crumbles.
Drain and return mixture to skillet.
Stir in chili seasoning and tomatoes. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheeses and olives. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: aunt beulah's pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites; add sugar and broken pecans.
Butter pie plate, then put crushed Ritz crackers in pie pan.
Spread egg white mixture to form pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Let cool, then add whipping cream sweetened to taste with sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Refrigerate.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mash, grind or run figs through a food mill.
Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Raspberry or blackberry may also be used.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, sausage, onion and garlic in oil. Drain off fat. Stir in all ingredients except chili beans and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in chili beans and simmer 10 more minutes. Serve with sour cream or cheese.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, combine the beans, soup and half of onions. Season with salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until heated. Sprinkle remaining onions on top and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Combine all ingredients; slow cook in crock-pot.
Serve over spaghetti. Note:
This thickens easily.
You may need to add water.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Be sure to seal well with Miracle Whip.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Using oil from the chops, liberally grease a casserole dish.
Line dish with rice; cover with undiluted soup and add milk.
Place chops on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare taco seasoning mix with ground beef and water according to package directions.
In 1-quart bowl, spread beef and layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve immediately with nacho chips.
Serves eight.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Beat egg until fluffy, add milk and mix.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add the eggs and milk to mixture to form a heavy batter (drop by spoonfuls into hot gravy and cook 15 minutes without taking off lid).

title: dolly parton salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and pudding in boiling water.
Chill until syrupy; fold in whipped topping, pineapple and the juice.
Add the well drained mandarin oranges.
Chill well until serving time. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: block beans
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Add tomato soup, tomato paste, barbecue sauce and catsup.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes; put in large roaster and add green beans, lima beans and wax beans, which have been drained.
Do not drain the chili beans or pork and beans but add to beef mixture along with brown sugar and mustard.
Mix well and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 25 servings.

title: gourmet meat balls
directions: Mix beef, sour cream and onion soup.
Add egg and crumbs. Form into balls.
Mix flour and paprika; roll balls in mixture. Brown slowly on all sides in butter.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over meat.
Cover pan and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening in a large bowl.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beating well at medium speed on an electric mixer, add eggs, one at a time.
Beating after each, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well and stir in extract.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll dough int 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Cool. Yields 4 dozen.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan and add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add buttermilk.
Let cool for awhile, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine for 30 seconds in microwave in glass cup.
Add salts and sauce.
Mix.

title: egg strata
directions: Put bread in square baking pan.
Melt Velveeta and butter; pour over bread.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over bread.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: pollo en casserole
directions: Lightly beat together egg and water.
Brush over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on surface, coating well.
Stir together sauce mix, tomato paste and water into shallow casserole dish.
Place chicken in sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve with pasta.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda, ginger and salt and sift together 3 times. Heat molasses. Add butter and stir until blended. Add vinegar. Add flour and blend well. Chill. Turn onto floured board. Roll 1/8-inch thick. Cut with large scalloped cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until onions are tender.
Add tomatoes and soup (not diluted).
Add rice and seasonings.
Let simmer about 5 minutes longer if too juicy.
Add pepper to taste. Put all ingredients in casserole dish; lay strips of cheese across top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion; mix with water and taco seasoning.
Spread the can of refried beans in a baking dish. Next, add the layer of hamburger and onion mixture.
Third layer is the taco sauce.
On top of that, layer the carton of sour cream.
Last, add the layer of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Serve with taco chips. Freezes well!

title: quick shrimp scampi
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and onion; cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp are lightly pink. Add basil; mix well. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve over hot cooked fettuccine or angel hair pasta. Serves 4.

title: fluffy frosting(non-cooked)
directions: Add salt and sugar to egg whites, and continue beating.
Add syrup and vanilla and blend until mixed.
Suggestion: Different food colors give a marble effect when added.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Slice apples and serve with dip.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown rice in butter. add bouillon. Bake in covered 1 1/2-quart casserole 30 minutes in a 375° oven. Stir in vegetables and nuts. Cover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: busy day vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in a large pan; add remaining ingredients.
Cover. Simmer slowly, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: honey butter
directions: Beat butter - do not substitute margarine - until creamy. Add honey until reach desired sweetness, then whip together for one minute.
Serve now, or refrigerate like regular butter.
Great with yeast rolls fresh from oven.

title: dip and twist
directions: You wil need containers for colored water and white paper towels or napkins.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ground ham, orange soda, Rice Krispies and mustard together.
Form into 2-inch balls.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar with juice from pineapple.
Bake ham balls for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven. Pour off grease.
(Can be put in microwave oven for 15 minutes and then drained.)
After pouring off grease, add the pineapple and juice mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, cocoa and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt into shortening mixture.
Refrigerate dough for 3 hours.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix ingredients (except chocolate chips) in order listed. Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place mixture in pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: low carb no taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef mixed with salt, pepper, garlic and cumin to your liking. Make a salad to your liking. Top with cooked bacon and ground beef mixture and top with the cheese of your choice.

title: johnny mozette
directions: Fry first 4 ingredients in as little oil as possible.
Cook until tender.
Add olives, noodles, tomato soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce.
Rinse each can with 1/2 can water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° about 2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: cheesy spinach pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Separate dough into 4 rectangles on smooth side of cutting board. Press seams to seal. Using spatula, spread each rectangle with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese to within 1/4-inch of edges. Top with 1 slice ham and spinach leaves. Starting at short side, roll up each rectangle; pinch edges to seal. Cut each roll crosswise into 6 slices for a total of 24 slices. Place cut side down. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove and serve warm. Yield: 24 pinwheels.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce and spices to boil.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs, added one at a time.
Add flour and applesauce. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy strawberry pie
directions: Pour milk in bowl and add pudding.
Slowly beat.
Blend in 1/2 Cool Whip.
Fold in quartered berries.
Pour
in
shell and chill. Top with remaining Cool Whip and halved berries.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, eggs, pineapple and vanilla. Sift in flour and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Mix together; pour over spinach, broccoli, cauliflower or any vegetables.
This sauce may be made in any quantity desired, so long as equal amounts of the 3 ingredients are used.

title: chicken fruit-n-nut salad
directions: On salad plates, arrange salad greens, chicken, apple and grapes.
Drizzle with dressing.
Garnish with walnuts.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Blend butter, flour, salt
and pepper in saucepan over low heat. Add tomatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add
milk and bring to a boil.
Add soda.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together, put in buttered casserole dish and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frost-on-the-pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to oil mixture, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin. Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting; sprinkle nuts over top.

title: chris' caramels
directions: Cook
all the ingredients, except the vanilla, to the soft ball stage, or 235°.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and pour into a buttered 8-inch pan.
When cold, turn out and cut into squares. Wrap each square individually in wax paper or plastic wrap.
For chocolate caramels, use 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 3 squares chocolate.

title: spaghetti with meat and vegetable sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cook meat, mushrooms, onion, carrot, green pepper, celery and garlic until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water or wine, basil, oregano, bay leaf, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon cold water.
Stir into sauce. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats
and buttermilk in a large bowl; let stand 1 hour.
Add
brown
sugar
and egg; mix well.
Combine flour, baking
powder,
baking
soda,
salt,
ground cinnamon, ground cloves and
ground mace.
Stir into oat mixture.
Stir in oil, grated
lemon
rind
and
raisins.
Spoon
into greased muffin tins, filling 1/2 full.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.
Wrap any leftovers in foil and freeze.
To reheat, thaw to room
temperature and bake in unopened foil at 350° for 15 minutes until hot.

title: orange canned sweet potatoes
directions: Pare and halve sweet potatoes.
Add boiling water and salt. Simmer in covered skillet until tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain off liquid, leaving 1/4 cup in skillet.
Dot potatoes with butter. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat (about 15 minutes), until glazed.
Baste often; turn potatoes once.
Serves 6.

title: chinese-style pork
directions: In a skillet, heat the oil.
Add the onion and cook until transparent.
Add the pork, chicken broth, celery, mushrooms and bean sprouts; simmer five minutes.

title: easy sweet pickles(makes about 5 pints)
directions: Pour fresh boiling water over whole cucumbers for 3 days. On 4th day, drain and slice cucumbers. Heat sugar, salt, vinegar and spices to boiling and pour over sliced cucumbers. Let stand for 2 days. On 3rd day, bring all to boil and can.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
While draining, season with garlic salt, onion salt, salt and pepper.
Suggest 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt and 1 teaspoon onion salt or to taste.
Mix soup and sour cream and stir in beans, then stir in cheese in small chunks.
Top with the buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion rings in butter until soft and transparent.
Pour in beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In individual soup bowls, add bread cubes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour hot soup on top of cubes and Parmesan cheese.
Top with Provolone cheese and cover to allow Provolone cheese to melt.

title: amish yum-a-setta
directions: Brown meat; add salt and pepper to taste, onion and brown sugar.
Add tomato soup and simmer.
Cook egg noodles according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add chicken soup.
Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture into casserole with cheese between layers.
(Nowadays, you can buy grated cheese, which works wonderfully.)

title: escalloped corn
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs into it and 8 ounces sour cream.
Add whole kernel corn and cream-style corn.
Mix corn bread mix.
Add salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake in shallow dish until knife or pick comes out of center clean.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Clean and devein shrimp; sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Add shrimp; increase heat and cook
5 minutes more, or until shrimp turn pink.
Add hot rice; mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and add with bacon drippings to shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: ham-bean chowder
directions: Saute onion and garlic clove in butter.
Cook adding 2 cups of shredded Cheddar cheese just before serving.
I always add 1 slice of smoked ham to each of the recipes.
Both recipes freeze well!

title: fruit dip
directions: Cut up fresh fruit of your choice.

title: olive-cheese-zucchini boats for 2
directions: Cut zucchini in half.
Scoop out and reserve pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop the pulp.
Saute in butter 5 minutes.
Stir in salt, bread crumbs and olives.
Spoon into shells and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Put in skillet with a little water.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole, pour 1 can pie filling at each end. Over pie filling, sprinkle pineapple plus juice.
Shake cake mix over fruit.
Top with coconut and walnuts or pecans.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from blueberries and pineapple.
Add to juice enough water to make 4 cups.
Heat 2 cups of the liquid to boiling.
Dissolve raspberry jello in it.
Add the remaining 2 cups liquid and fruit.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Let jell slightly.
Then fold in whipped cream.
Let jell for 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: orange bisque
directions: Mix 1 cup water with gelatin and bring to a boil.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, orange juice and lemon juice together.
Mix powdered milk with 2 5/8 cups water together with blender.
Mix gelatin in mixture.
Blend all ingredients.
Pour in long dish; let set.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pistachio pudding mix into crushed pineapple; mix well. Add 1 cup marshmallows and carton of Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: haole laulau
directions: Place half of the spinach in the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pork with garlic and arrange on top of the spinach.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange remaining spinach over the pork pieces. Cover pan with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Arrange yams on top and dot with butter.
Continue baking 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake #2
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and blend well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool completely before removing from pan.

title: nut cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar, mixing until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on greased baking sheet in oven preheated to 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While still warm, roll cookies in additional sugar, then cool completely on rack.

title: herbed beer bread and herbed butter
directions: Mix the first four ingredients for one minute with a wooden spoon.
Pour into bread pan. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. Remove from oven and pour 1/2 stick melted oleo over the top. Return to oven for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and remove from pan.
Mix the last three ingredients together to use as spread on the cooled sliced bread.

title: simple chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Follow recipe on the cake mix box for mixing and baking the cake.
Bake two layers.
When cake is baked, turn on baking rack until cool.
Mix pistachio instant pudding mix as directed on the box.
Let chill until set.
(You can make the pudding before time to use it.)
Take the pudding mix after it has set and spread on one layer of cake.
Place the other layer on top of first layer. Spread chocolate frosting on top and sides of cake.

title: scrumptious chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs and buttermilk. Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture. Add vanilla and boiling water. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Test with toothpick. Frost with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting.

title: banana nut tea bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after each.
Add vanilla and stir in bananas.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda and blend into banana mixture 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir in nuts.
Gently fold in sour cream (the magic ingredient that makes it so moist).
Pour mixture into 9x5x3 greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.	Cool in pan for 20 minutes before turning onto a rack.
(If you use the mini loaf pans (4), baking time is approximately 35-40 minutes.)

title: gran's cabbage slaw
directions: 1 med. head of cabbage, shredded

title: sour cream bars
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil until margarine melts, then add the flour, sugar, sour cream, eggs and baking soda.

title: "grama todd's chili sauce"
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cook tomatoes down a little, then add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Can.
Use an approved method.

title: mexican style cornbread
directions: In 2-quart saucepan melt Crisco.
Add onions and cook over medium heat until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato, green chilies, water and garlic powder.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and continue cooking for 3 minutes or until hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with corn chips.
Cut each tamale into 5 portions.
Layer tamales, rice and onion over chips.
Spread chili over top layer; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, with foil for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pinto beans
directions: Cover beans with water (about 1 to 2 inches above beans).
Cook for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add all ingredients; add enough water to cover beans.
Cook 2 more hours or until done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cake:
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately with sugar and shortening mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut and bake in three 9-inch pans for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Use nonstick spray coating.
Spray only the bottom of a 2-quart square baking dish with nonstick coating.
Combine flour, almonds and baking powder.
Heat and stir butter and unsweetened chocolate over medium heat until melted.
Stir into sugar, eggs, egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat by hand until just combined.
Stir into flour mixture.
Spread mixture into prepared baking dish sprinkled with candy-coated pieces.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cook in pair on rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: iced chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, 2 at a time. Add vanilla and Hershey's chocolate. Then add sifted flour and baking powder. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and celery, saute.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly for 25 minutes.

title: rick's lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly and drain.
Add next three ingredients and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter rice on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place pieces of chicken, skin side up, on top of rice.
Combine mushroom soup, water and onion soup. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Drain pineapple until almost dry. Squeeze small amounts between hands at least 3 or 4 times until no more juice remains. Whip together cream cheese, sugar and milk; stir in pineapple. Fold into Cool Whip and stir in nuts. Refrigerate 1 or 2 hours before serving. Can be made a day before using. Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chickumber chowder
directions: In a three quart saucepan, saute onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cucumber.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour half the mixture at a time into a blender or food processor.
Cover and blend on medium for 30 seconds.
Return all the mixture to saucepan.

title: chicken broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or deep skillet; add chicken cubes and stir-fry until half cooked.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts and onion.
Stir-fry.
Add chicken broth, soy sauce and blended cornstarch, cooking until thickened.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: pepsi-cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in frying pan, skin side down.
Pour over chicken catsup and pepsi.
Cover and bring to boil.
Turn heat down on low and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: party potatoes
directions: Put frozen potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, bananas and sour cream.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend into cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 28 muffins.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer, mix all ingredients accordingly.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in the middle rack at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly with fingers or by inserting a knife in the middle of cake comes out clean.
Cool the pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes.
With a spatula loosen the edges; turn out on plate.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 2-quart glass oblong baking dish. Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over butter; add 1 large can peaches and some juice.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
After baking a few minutes, can sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: swiss apple pie
directions: Mix together, put in greased pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender. In a bowl, alternate layers of carrots, pepper and onion. Blend well the soup, oil, sugar, vinegar and mustard. Pour over carrots. Bake in medium oven until onions and peppers are soft. Or serve cold by cooking carrots slightly (leave crisp) and marinate with peppers and onions overnight.

title: egg custard(dessert)
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter together to a simmer point.
Pour over beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake until done.

title: taco sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Mix together, simmer about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Can use immediately or will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle cheese over bottom of crust. Top with refried beans and sausage cut into small bits.
Combine half and half and egg in small bowl.
Whip eggs slightly.
Add green chilies and onion and stir again.
Pour this mixture over other layered ingredients in pie pan.
Bake 1 hour or until mixture is firm.
Optional:
May add avocados, tomatoes and sour cream to top if desired.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat the margarine, sugar and eggs until smooth.
At low speed, beat sour cream and vanilla into the egg mixture.
By hand, stir in flour mixture and coconut.
Drop batter by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, then add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix the 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Grease a tube pan, put in half the batter, then sprinkle half the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Then, put in the rest of the batter and sprinkle the rest of sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done when tested with tester.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs, oil, pineapple and almond extract. Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 11 x 15-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes if using 9 x 13-inch pan (if using 11 x 15-inch pan bake 25 minutes) or until springs back from touch.
Remove from oven and pour icing over hot cake. Sprinkle coconut on top and press in.
Let cool 45 minutes before serving.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour into your buttered pan.
Pour fruit (apples or cherries) on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form when beater is raised slowly.
Gently fold in cheese mixture just until well combined with egg whites.
Shape into balls, using level tablespoon for each.
Roll in bread crumbs on waxed paper.

title: walnut sweet potatoes
directions: Mix with a hand mixer.
Pour into a glass pan.
(Use Pam on bottom).

title: cheese potato delight
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam. Place potatoes in it and put in oven.
Melt butter and mix corn flakes in it.
Set aside.

title: icebox delight
directions: Combine and bring to boil butter, milk, sugar and egg.
Mix in another bowl:
graham cracker crumbs, black walnuts and coconut. Pour hot mixture over this and mix well.
Line long pan with graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and spread.
Add graham cracker crumbs over this.

title: super baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole and lay bacon on top.
Bake uncovered until mixture thickens and bacon is thoroughly cooked at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blushing pink soda
directions: Mix first three ingredients in tall glass.
Stir in 1/4 cup strawberry soda.
Add additional ice cream and soda to fill to the top of the glass.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Cook for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix orange juice and sugar together.
When cake is almost cooled, gently poke holes in cake with a fork.
Pour the juice mixture around (cake is still in pan).
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top after cake has been removed from pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Can serve with chips or vegetables.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, crumble hamburger. Tear bread into small chunks.
Add egg, garlic, seasoned salt and 1/2 cup picante sauce.
Mix well.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: In 5 qt.
Dutch oven melt margarine and marshmallows.
Mix in vanilla and food color.
Stir in frosted flakes until well coated. Spoon onto greased pan and decorate with 3 cinnamon candies.
May also make 1 large wreath.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat; stirring only until sugar dissolves.
Stir in coloring while cooking.
When the candy reaches 280°, stir in the flavoring oil.
When the candy reaches 290°, quickly pour into 3 mini ice cube trays or candy trays.
Let cool and harden about 4 hours.
Twist trays to pop candy out.
Store in airtight container.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Stir in ground venison, mushrooms, seasonings and flour; saute 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes more.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat and serve with rice or noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
In a bag, put the 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put biscuit pieces in bag and shake.
Layer the "sugared" biscuits in a greased Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Boil the brown sugar and butter and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and sausages with onion in a skillet.
Place other ingredients in a Dutch oven and bring to a slow boil.
Add meat mixture and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain and finely chop artichokes.
Mix with other ingredients. Spray a shallow pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: A good many husbands are utterly spoiled by mismanagement. Some women go about it as if their husbands were bladders, and blow them up.
Others keep them constantly in hot water.
Others let them freeze by their carelessness and indifference.
Some keep them in a stew, by irritating ways and words.
Others roast them. Some keep them in a pickle all their lives.
It cannot be supposed that any husband will be tender and good, managed in this way, but they are really delicious when properly treated.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cheese.
In a separate bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture at once and stir only until flour is dampened.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until light brown; drain off fat.
Add onions and green pepper; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: little hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into three pieces.
Mix all ingredients together. Cook at 350° until sauce gets thick and hot dogs are done.

title: batter for fried mushrooms
directions: Clean and wash mushrooms; mix together first 4 ingredients. Dip mushrooms in batter.
Fry at 350° until golden brown.

title: aunt vera's carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Chop onion, celery and garlic in food processor and add to saucepan.
Chop potatoes and carrots in food processor.
