Combine all ingredients in slow cooker on high for 4 hours or low all day or in pot on back burner and simmer all day.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: banana slush punch
directions: In a blender, dissolve 4 cups sugar in 6 cups hot water (add food coloring, if desired).
Add juices directly from the cans; add cut up bananas and pineapple.
Freeze.
To serve, put the frozen mixture into a punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over it and mix slowly so mixture becomes slushy.
Yield:
60 servings.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place sugar in food processor and process until very fine.
Add butter.
Pulse until sugar disappears.
Add flour, pulse until flour disappears.
Mixture will be moist and crumbly.
Place into a plastic bag.
Press together to form dough.

title: fried chicken i
directions: Wash chicken. Pat excess water from chicken with a paper towel. Salt and pepper chicken; roll in flour, coating both sides. Fry in hot oil in a large frying pan, cooking on medium heat, until both sides are golden brown. Remove and drain on paper towels. Continue cooking chicken until all chicken has been cooked.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook until syrup reaches the first ball stage (254° on a candy thermometer).
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, moist peaks form when beaters are raised.
Add half the syrup gradually to egg whites, beating constantly.
Return remaining syrup to stove to boil up again, then gradually beat into egg whites.
Continue beating until dry.
Beat in vanilla and nuts by hand.
Add coloring and cherries if desired.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: humus tahini
directions: Pulverize beans in a blender. Add tahini sauce and lemon juice slowly. Whip until smooth.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed. In a salad bowl, add cooled rice chopped onion, mustard, salad dressing or mayo, and salt. Mix well, cover and chill. Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.

title: linguini with tuna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil, add tomato sauce and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add Tonno tuna (do not drain), pepper and cheese.
Cook on very low heat for 15 minutes.
Cook linguini, drain well.
Pour tomato and tuna ingredients over linguini.
Add more cheese if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in baked pie shells.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch on high until clear.
Turn off fire and add jello. Stir.
Then cool some.
Pour over strawberries and refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat them separately and fold into other ingredients.
Bake in buttered 9-inch pie pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip when cool.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onion. In a small bowl, combine sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli; toss to coat.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and sunflower seeds; toss.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: venison jerky
directions: Use 1/4-inch thick strips venison and marinate overnight. Bake at 140° to 150° for approximately 6 hours.
Turn after 2 hours.
If you use smoker, cut liquid smoke to 1 teaspoon.

title: jessie's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco (I use butter-flavored) until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes on medium.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Stir-fry in oil for 5 minutes. Add chopped
onion
and fry for 2 minutes more.
In casserole dish layer crumbs, chicken, potatoes and onion.
Add broth and bake for 15 minutes or 5 minutes microwave.

title: pralines
directions: Boil until firm ball, 118° to 120°. Take off stove. Stir in pecans; stir until a glaze. Add vanilla. Spoon on waxed paper.

title: a la crema ae ou froumai(pasta with cream and parmesan)
directions: Beat 6 ounces softened butter with
a wooden spoon until creamed.
Gradually incorporate the cream and grated Parmesan. Allow to reach room temperature 15 minutes before use.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine packed cheese, cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into ball shapes, using cold pack containers coated with margarine or lined with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm; unmold.
Place either chopped parsley or strips of pimiento on if you like.

title: off the farm
directions: Melt bacon drippings in a heavy skillet and add onion, garlic, beef and pork.
Brown meat on all sides.
Cover and allow to steam about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano, bay leaves and chili powder.
Mix flour with a bit of cold water and stir into pot.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Then add olives, water and kidney beans. Simmer 30 more minutes, adding more water if necessary.
This one is on the mild side as chilis go.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Cook one minute and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and whip until thick.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil the unpeeled potatoes in salted water.
Let cool; peel, then dice or slice.
Dice the onion and hard-boiled eggs.
Cut the bacon into bite sized pieces before frying until crispy.
Into the grease from the bacon, add mixture of 2 beaten eggs, the mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Pour hot dressing over potatoes and add pickle relish to taste.
Serve warm.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into 3 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine crumbs and margarine and sprinkle on casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top of crumbs and margarine.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Place vegetables in broth; bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes or until softened.
Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour. Add milk.
Simmer until thick, about 5 minutes, stirring often. Add Cheddar cheese, stirring constantly until melted.
Add chicken to broth mixture.
Add cheese mixture to broth mixture.
Stir. Serve.

title: meatballs with a tang
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Put into a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 2-inch pan.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: butterfly crackers
directions: Melt together margarine and sugar.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add nuts.
Dab mixture on Socialite crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs deluxe en croute
directions: Make scrambled eggs:
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
With rotary beater, beat just until combined.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Pour in egg mixture.
Cook over low heat.
As eggs start to set on bottom, scramble.
Add cheese and chives; cook until eggs are moist and shiny but no longer runny.
Split bread in 1/2 lengthwise.
With fork, scoop some of bread out from inside of loaf.
Brush inside of loaf after scooping with melted butter.
Spoon eggs into hot bread and serve. Makes 10.

title: thelma's blackberry cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add blackberries and juice.
Sift flour with cocoa, soda and spices. Add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sifted mixture of soda and flour alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt cheese in milk.
Add soup, eggs and pimentos.
Pour over well drained asparagus in casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, folding in the stiffly beaten whites last.
Bake mixture into a well-greased and crumbed pan and bake in moderately hot oven for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Serve with white sauce.

title: lime jello
directions: Make Jell-O using pineapple juice with water; add creme cheese while warm and beat well.
Chill until partially set and add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: sizzling cheese appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Spread mix on bread. Broil 4 inches from heat until cheese melts and it is brown. Makes approximately 36 servings.

title: punch
directions: I freeze part of this into ice cubes and pour the rest over the frozen ice cups to serve cold.
Serves 40.

title: turkey super dressing
directions: Saute ground turkey.
When turkey is lightly browned, add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Combine bread cubes, salt, sage and pepper.

title: brownstone front cake
directions: Melt cocoa and soda in warm water.
Set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Add cocoa mixture.
Bake in three greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350°.
Bake a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake 9-inch layers for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out of center clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl until well blended.
Add sugar, syrup, pecans, vanilla and salt.
Stir together until well mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.	Add brown sugar and beat well.
Let cool.
Add eggs and blend.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.	Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased pan.	Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick and easy pot pie
directions: Prepare pie crust per instructions on box.
Cook chicken or meat.
Boil veggies separately or microwave.
Combine cooked meat and veggies in single layer of pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup gravy with 1/2 cup water; add to pie.
Cover with remaining crust according to box and bake at 350° oven until golden brown.
Top with cream of chicken or mushroom soup.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly oil a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in pineapple and juice, spreading it over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cherries over layer, then coconut layer.
Sprinkle box of cake mix on top.
Cut margarine into slices, and dot over cake mix, covering well. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 300° for one hour until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken with salt.
When done, skin and dice.
Dice vegetables and cook in microwave dish with 1 cup water and 1 tablespoon oil until almost done.
Grease large pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups Bisquick with milk until thin enough to pour.
Cover bottom of pan.
Put 4 tablespoons of mixture in pie; pour all ingredients in pan and cover top with rest of mixture.
Use more broth if needed.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put a layer of eggs, oleo, cream of mushroom soup, beans and crackers.
Repeat.
Save some crackers to sprinkle on top.
Dot with oleo.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet cabbage(servings: 4)
directions: Heat the oil in a large frypan about 20 minutes before serving time.
Add ingredients and cook over medium to low heat, about 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Cover pan during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Stir once or twice.
Serve immediately. (Vegetables will be crisp.)

title: oatmeal drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, orange peel, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and raisins and stir to form thick lumpy batter.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown, 17 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: dorchester fudge
directions: Cut each chocolate square into 4 pieces.
Combine sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chocolate to remaining ingredients.
Carefully add boiling sugar syrup; stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill; cut into squares. Makes 36.

title: white clam sauce(microwave)
directions: Drain clams; reserve 1/4 cup juice.
In 1-quart microwave casserole (or Pyrex measuring cup), cook onions, garlic and margarine, covered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in flour and pepper. Add milk.

Cook, uncovered, on High 3 to 5 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring after each minute. Add clams, reserved juice, olives and parsley. Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes more or until mixture is heated through. Serve immediately on linguine.
Serves 2.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Cook in sugar on high, stirring often.
When it begins sticking to the bottom of pot, stir in juice from 1/2 of a lemon and cook for a few more minutes. Put in jar and seal.
Makes 1 pint.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese, Equal and peanut butter together; mix well. Add milk slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell and chill until firm.
Mix 1 tablespoon peanut butter and 1 tablespoon flour together.
Crumble over top of pie.
Diabetic Exchanges:
1 milk; 1/2 fat; 1 starch.

title: charged-up chocolate syrup cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is hot, pour on 1/2 to 3/4 can of chocolate syrup and whole can of milk.
Mix remaining chocolate syrup with whipped topping.
When cake has completely cooled, spread mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Place all ingredients into blender.
Blend 7 minutes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Preheat oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with fruit.

title: egg substitute
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use as a substitute for 1 egg.
Do not cook too fast.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add pineapple and juice, add blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until set.

title: beer marinade for cooked brats
directions: Heat the broth until bubbling.
Put cooked brats in broth for about 1/2 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, dot with 3 teaspoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon egg white pecans
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add vanilla, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip pecans in mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all together and chill.

title: potato poncho
directions: Either bake potatoes in microwave or oven.
Use whichever is more convenient to you.
Microwave is quicker; 12 minutes on each side of the potato.
Check for doneness.
Slice potatoes and put your amount of butter or margarine on them.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix with taco packets, by the directions. Lay sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Cover with taco meat.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Spray bundt pan with Pam and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, nectar, and eggs. Pour into prepared pan and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: green beans with sour cream sauce
directions: Wash, trim and French-cut diagonally, cut whole beans into inch lengths. Cook in boiling salted water for 5 to 7 minutes for French or 10 to 15 minutes for 2-inch pieces, until tender-crisp. Drain well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place first 4 ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add raw peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly, while continuing to boil.
Cook until peanuts are brown and stop popping.
Add coconut and soda.
Stir and quickly pour onto well-buttered biscuit pan. Cool and break up.
Store in airtight container.

title: spinach squares
directions: Wash, cook and drain spinach well.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add butter, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese, onion and spinach.
Spoon mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and level off.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool off for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares. These freeze well.
Can defrost and reheat for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and the macaroni.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Arrange tomato slices over top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy parmesan cheese sauce
directions: Microwave cream cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese in 1-quart container on medium (50%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until sauce is smooth. Stir every 2 minutes. Stir in pepper and toss with cooked hot pasta.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Flour and season.
Fry and drain on paper towel.
In large pot, put steak, soup and small amount of water.
Cover and let simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: herb-seasoned popcorn
directions: In small bowl, combine margarine, basil, oregano and cayenne. Pour evenly over popcorn which is placed in large bowl. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss gently.
Makes 6 cups.

title: almond caramels
directions: Spread bottom and sides of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with butter or margarine.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine granulated sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, light cream and 4 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to firm ball stage (248°).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and almonds. Turn into prepared pan; cool.
Cut into squares.
Wrap each. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken plantation
directions: Stew chicken until it falls off bone.
Remove from bone and cut into tiny pieces.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients with chicken and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread on top. Cook in 345° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off oranges and pineapple.
Del Monte brand cocktail is best.
Mix all ingredients lightly.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Combine and sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to first mixture along with the chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. The pan may be a little larger but shouldn't be any smaller.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut cream candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Cool thoroughly.

title: chocolate silk
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients well and flatten in a 10 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Mix last three ingredients.
Mix with drained fruit.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: special k peanut butter bars
directions: In saucepan, mix Karo and sugar; bring to a boil for 1 minute (rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add to cereal and mix well.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: haystacks
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and blend quickly. Crush saltines and chop pecans in large mixing bowl.
Stir in mixture quickly and put on wax paper, one tablespoon and let cool.

title: quick and easy dump cake
directions: Pour fruit (large can) in bottom of baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan. Add dry cake mix.
Place pats of margarine over the top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Delicious plain or with Cool Whip topping or with ice cream.
(Pie filling may be substituted for fruit.)

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Combine beef and soup mix in skillet; brown over medium-high heat until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in cheese; set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough.
Cut each crescent in half making 16 triangles from each package.
Place a heaping teaspoonful of meat mixture on each triangle; roll to enclose.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, tucking point of dough under roll.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm or let cool and freeze.
To serve after thawing, warm in preheated 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chop and wild rice casserole
directions: Put raw rice and seasoning mix in casserole dish.
Brown pork chops in oil on both sides.
Place single layered on raw rice.
On each pork chop, place 1 slice each onion, green pepper and tomato. Pour beef broth over this.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: rule for meringue(never fails)
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until they stand up in peaks and are stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, very slowly, 1/2 at a time. Beat constantly.
Beat in vanilla.
Spread on pie and bake in a slow oven, at 300°, for about 10 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; mix well.

title: spinach and bacon quiche(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prebake shell.
Cook bacon crisp and drain.
Saute onions slowly in the butter or oleo (I use 2 tablespoons bacon drippings) and onions until almost tender.
Add the minced garlic and continue until the garlic begins to change color.
Strew the grated Swiss cheese (1/4 cup) in bottom of shell. Break up the pieces of bacon and strew over the Swiss cheese. Sprinkle a little grated Swiss over the bacon.

title: carrot soup
directions: Scrub carrots well. Peel potatoes and onions. Cut carrots and potatoes into pieces; chop onion and celery. Pressure cook, or boil vegetables, until soft.

title: no roll crust
directions: When ingredients are combined.
Press into pie pan with hand. This makes one (9-inch) pie crust.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning. simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough onto bottom of pizza pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 375 degrees 10 - 12 minutes.
Cover with meat mixture, then velveeta.
Continue to bake until cheese melts.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Grease and flour wax paper in pan.
Pour mixture and bake on a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn into a dish towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll it up.
Cool and unroll, fill, reroll and chill.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Slightly defrost lemonade and strawberries and blend together in blender.
Pour into a plastic container and freeze.
Four hours before serving, defrost at room temperature.
Place in punch bowl and pour 7-Up over mixture.
Garnish with fresh strawberries or add a package of frozen strawberries.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Stir in cheese. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Makes 3 cups. Keeps up to 3 weeks.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg. Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Combine molasses and water.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with the liquid mixture, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: "philly" miracle whip wreath
directions: Variation:
Substitute 1/2 cup fine chopped ham, 1/4 cup chopped green pepper and 1/4 cup chopped onion for bacon and green onion.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, celery, onions, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Top with cracker crumbs and oleo.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken almond rice
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown almonds in margarine and remove from pan after browning.
Add onions and mushrooms to remaining margarine and saute.
When slightly browned, add herbs, lemon juice and sherry. Return almonds to onion mixture and stir together.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Lift cooked chicken out of sauce.
Gently stir cooked rice into sauce to serve.
Spoon rice mixture on platter.
Place chicken on top of rice and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: key lime pie
directions: Separate eggs, saving both yolk and whites.
Combine lime juice, egg yolks and condensed milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue from egg whites.
Bake at 350° for a few minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble or cut into small pieces before cooking and cook until well done.
Cook Minute rice according to directions on box.
Put tomatoes and 1/2 of cheese (cut in small pieces) in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add bacon pieces and rice.
Stir until well mixed.
Add rest of cheese, cut in small pieces, and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until slightly browned on top.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown ground beef with onion and pepper; simmer 10 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: granny's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter, cream cheese and margarine together. Add powdered sugar and milk; mix well.
Fold in topping.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with carrots, celery and onion.
Drain.
Throw carrots and celery away.
Cut up chicken and place in broth.
Add 1/3 cup flour, 2 tablespoons of Good Seasons Italian dressing and eggs.
Add to chicken; add seasoned salt, also.
Take 6 cups flour, 3 tablespoons butter and little of chicken broth and mix together.
Roll out the dumpling mix, then cut in strips and place in chicken and cook until done.

title: onion burgers
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Add flour and soup.
Let simmer until slightly thickened.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet, remove bacon, but leave grease in pan. Brown beef and onion in grease.
Add everything except beans and simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until thick, or cover with wax paper and microwave 20 minutes, or cook 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons of sugar and margarine. Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Mix until thickened.
Spoon carefully over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually; beat until glossy.
Fold in flour, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Line baking sheet with greased heavy brown paper.
Drop mixture by teaspoons on paper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: broiled fish with pacifica sauce
directions: Arrange the fish in a single layer in heat- proof platter or shallow baking pan. In small saucepan combine lemon juice, butter, onion, brown, sugar, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Heat, stirring, till blended. Pour sauce over fish. Preheat broiler. Broil fish slowly, about 4 inches from the flame, basting 2 or 3 times with sauce till fish is browned and will flake when tested with fork. Sprinkle with paprika after final basting. Arrange cooked baby carrots and asparagus spears around edge of platter and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: *peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in heavy, deep pot.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Cook over low heat until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased dish.
Cut into squares.

title: favorite pinto beans
directions: Cook beans for 2 hours.
Brown ground beef.
Add together with all other ingredients and continue simmering for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter almond balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and butter. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.
Meanwhile, melt the almond coating in a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl. Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Break the eggs into a bowl; warm to lukewarm without drying out.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat the eggs with the baking powder and salt until thick and very pale.
Gradually beat in the sugar; continue to beat until thick.
Beat in the vanilla.
Sift the flour twice; fold into the egg mixture.
Spread the mixture over a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan that has been greased, lined with wax paper and greased again.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden. Turn out onto a cloth towel sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Peel off paper.
Roll up from the long side, enclosing the towel.
Cool on a rack.
When cake is cool, unroll, spread with preserves and reroll without the towel.
Serve in slices.
Makes 10 servings.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine ingredients and press into 8-inch or 9-inch pan. Refrigerate 1 hour before filling.
Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 1.5 g, fat 3.7 g, calories 84.
Each serving 1/8 pie crust, exchange per serving: 1/8 crust = 1 fruit, 1 fat.

title: vegetable stuffed mushrooms(low-fat, low calories, low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Wash and pat dry mushrooms. Twist off stems (set caps aside) and mince stems. In skillet, melt margarine over moderate heat; add green onions, celery and mushroom stems. Cook uncovered, stirring often until vegetables are soft (about 5 minutes). Add tomato, marjoram and pepper. Cook covered 5 minutes. Stir in bread crumbs and remove skillet from heat. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps, mounding it up slightly. In lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, arrange mushrooms in single layer. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: graham cracker muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the crumbled crackers and milk. Stir together sugar, salt, flour and baking powder.
Add raisins, then add graham mixture.
Stir in butter and egg until smooth. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar
and	oil.
Blend. Add carrots and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon and
nuts.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch cake pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Boil water until bubbling hot.
(Hot water cooks the meal.) Slowly add water to dry mixture.
Texture should be firm.
Wet hands and form meal into oval shape.
Place in hot oil frying until golden brown.

title: ham and cheese croquettes
directions: Mix eggs and ham.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Slowly stir in milk.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese, parsley and egg and ham mixture.
Blend well.
Cool.
When mixture is cold, shape into croquettes.
Dip in beaten eggs and roll in breadcrumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: jellied chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on 1/2 cup chicken broth to soften.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining broth.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir chicken, lemon juice, celery, olives, onion and salt into gelatin.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with pimiento and tomato wedges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter about 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, bouillon cubes, soup, milk, almonds and Minute rice in order given.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add cut-up chicken and chopped eggs.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 1 teaspoon vinegar to milk; let stand 5 minutes.

title: pork chops in sour cream gravy
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter in a heavy skillet.
Remove mushrooms and brown pork chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper; add 1/2 cup water, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms. Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Remove chops and keep warm. Prepare gravy in juice with mushrooms in skillet.
Mix flour and remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add to the juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Serve at once over pork chops.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: italian sausage and potatoes
directions: Heat
oven

Cut
sausage
into
or 4-inch pieces.
Pierce with fork.
Add oil to roaster.
Place sausage in it and cook in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn sausage and pierce other
side.
Cook
another
15 to 20 minutes.

oven and

reserving about 2 tablespoons in roaster.
Add potatoes; season and add bell pepper and onion. Add
a little more seasoning.
Cover with roaster lid and cook about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and gently stir to combine all.

to add more seasoning.) Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: pickle rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion juice to make a spread. Trim bread and spread a small amount of cheese mixture on slices. Place on wax paper.
Add pickle to top of cheese mixture and roll bread around pickle.
Roll in wax paper and twist ends together. Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
When ready to serve, slice into desired size pieces.

title: fabulous carrot cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, crushed pineapple and juice, oil, vanilla, salt, coconut, carrots and pecans.
Add dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Line 3 (8-inch) cake pans with waxed paper.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool on racks for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Halve and pit avocados and scoop out flesh into a bowl.
Mash avocado to desired consistency and mix in remaining ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for about one hour before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Coat beef with flour mixture. Brown in
hot shortening.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and broth to meat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Stir in
vegetables,
except
peas.
Cover
and cook about 15
minutes more.
Add
peas
and
cook 8 more minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Combine all the ingredients and pour over Top Round London Broil.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: almond crab appetizer
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put in microwave just to heat.
Top with toasted, slivered almonds.
Serve on small slices of bread or crackers.

title: chicken balls
directions: Boil cut up chicken and potatoes in small amount of water with salt added.
When chicken is tender, pull off bones and cut in small pieces.
Add potatoes, peppers and Tony Chachere to taste. Form in balls, roll in flour and fry in fat.
Drain and serve.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Drain onions.
Add cheese with a small amount of milk. Thicken with thin white sauce.
Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Put in oven until bread crumbs are a golden brown.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add flour and flavorings; continue beating 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake at 300° about 1 1/2 hours or until tested done in tube pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: grandmother's famous orange-cranberry bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add eggs, orange peel and juice all at once; stir just until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Use at room temperature.
Do not thaw.
Spread the 2 cans of bean dip in casserole dish; spread avocado
dip over bean dip. Mix sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocado dip.
Spread grated cheese over sour cream mixture; sprinkle chopped green onions, tomatoes and ripe olives on top.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini, onions, carrots and peppers through food grinder using medium blade.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight (I let stand about 3 to 4 hours).
In morning, drain and rinse well with cold water.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil in a large kettle.
Add the ground vegetables, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars. Makes 7 pints.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples into baking dish.
Mix butter, flour, brown sugar and oats.
Heat and pour on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm, good with vanilla ice cream.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
When both are well mixed, put together in one large bowl and mix.
Put into wax paper-lined loaf pans or angel food cake pan.
Cover with cloth and put in refrigerator to set for 7 days.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: ponche breakfast drink
directions: Put banana, milk, vanilla and sugar in blender.
Mix thoroughly.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour into oiled tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: remedy reward's famous cheese bread
directions: Split loaf of French bread.
Finely chop green onions (tops and all).
Mix onions, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Spread mixture evenly over the bread and put under broiler.
Watch carefully!
Slice and serve to great raves!!
Remedy loves to eat large amounts of this - honest!

title: nutty fingers
directions: Sift 1/2 box sugar into shallow pan.
Measure the 4 tablespoons into another bowl and save remainder of sugar for rolling Nutty Fingers.
Cream butter and sugar well; add flour and pecans.
Shape into finger size rolls and cook until lightly brown at 250° to 300°.
Do not overcook.
Remove from oven and cool slightly before rolling in remaining sugar.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: merry christmas brew
directions: Combine sugar, salt, spices and water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine apple juice and fruit slices in a large saucepan.
Heat gently.
Strain hot spice liquid into apple juice and serve warm.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, toss noodles with Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, spoon enough sauce to cover bottom.
Layer 1/2 the noodle mixture and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Roll into pencil shape about 4 inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: feta cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate about 1 to 2 hours before serving.
This recipe is great as a dip with pita bread or sliced cucumbers and onions.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in morsels and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.
Dump in pineapple in pan; spread out.
Dump in cherry pie filling; spread around. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top and bake.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach and squeeze all the water out.
In a large bowl mix sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mixes; stir until well blended.
Add spinach and mix well.
Chill and serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers or chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and Karo.
Cook to hard ball stage (256°).
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Cook to light crack stage (275°).
Pour over popcorn and mix quickly.
Press into balls with greased hands.

title: layered garden salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, eggs, peas
and
bacon in 9 x 13-inch dish in order given.
Mix salad
dressing
and
sugar and add enough milk or cream to make a smooth spreading consistency. Spread over salad like a frosting.
Top with grated
cheese. Refrigerate
to 12 hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a large baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and put pineapple slices on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish in order given.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: easy cucumber pickle *
directions: Add washed and sliced cucumbers to lime and water mixture and soak overnight.
Then pour off this water, add fresh water to cover cucumbers and allow to soak for 3 hours.
Pour off this water and pour sugar and vinegar over cucumbers.
Bring to a boil and boil for 35 minutes.
Add amount of pickle spice desired, either loose or tied in a cloth.
Put in warm jars and seal.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in crock-pot on high until all melted.
Add the peanuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: jelly roll coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until light and fluffy. Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Spread 2/3 of batter in 11 x 15-inch greased baking pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Drop remainder of batter on top in small bits here and there.
While still warm, drizzle with glaze (one 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 to 2 tablespoons milk and flavor with almond extract).
Bake 40 minutes.

title: creamsicle punch
directions: Blenderize all of the ingredients.

title: pork scallopini
directions: Place meat between wax paper and pound.
Grate the rind of 1 orange and remove remaining skin.
Peel the 2nd orange; cut each in half and half again.
Season the pork with pepper.
Dip in flour and cook in skillet 4 or 5 minutes per side.
Add onion, broth, grated rind and juice.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add orange halves; heat and serve.
Serves 4.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Cut fresh green beans into 1-inch pieces and cook as directed; drain.
Cook onion, celery and garlic in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in herbs.
Add beans; toss lightly.
Cover; heat through.
Season with salt.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: burgundy cran-apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cranberry sauce and add apple cider and Burgundy, mixing well.
Chill until partially congealed; fold in apples.
Pour into a 6 cup mold and chill until firm.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown
ground
beef
and
drain
off
fat.
Add onions, tomato sauce
and
tomatoes.
Stir in pepper, salt and sugar. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles;
drain and fold in sour cream
and cream cheese.
Stir into sauce mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fudge (hershey)
directions: Cook together the sugar and Pet cream.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add margarine, chocolate and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Add nuts.

title: quick chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: In large saucepan, combine the sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add cereal and mix thoroughly.
Spread into 13 x 9 greased pan.
Pour chocolate chips over top, spreading evenly and put under broiler for only a few minutes and spread over all.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over crackers; stir to coat. Place in 200° oven for 2 hours.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Whip in 2 cups flour and let rest 10 minutes.
Add eggs, yeast and remaining flour. Mix until smooth.
Let raise 45 minutes.

title: daphne croal's cheesy shrimp
directions: Melt all but 6 slices of cheese in large casserole dish with Ro-Tel tomatoes (I used the microwave).
Saute sliced mushrooms in butter (I used 2 sticks).
Season mushrooms to your own personal taste.
After cheese has been melted and mushrooms sauteed, combine everything in large casserole dish, place the remaining 6 slices of cheese on top and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until shrimp are done.

title: mom's marble cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and powder and add alternately with milk; add vanilla.
Grease and flour baking pan (angel food cake pan).
Pour 2/3 of batter in pan. Mix chocolate syrup with remaining batter and then add to batter in pan.
Fold together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon french toast
directions: Day before, prepare apples and French toast.
In large skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Add apple slices and cook, stirring occasionally until tender.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and cinnamon to apples.
Cook, stirring until brown sugar dissolves. Put apple mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spread to even layer.
Arrange bread slices in one layer on top of apple mixture. In medium size bowl, with fork, beat eggs, milk and vanilla until well mixed; pour over bread slices.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: jif peanut butter cookies(won first place blue ribbon state fair 1993)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together the brown sugar, Jif and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Beat until well mixed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in a crisscross pattern with tines of a fork (dip fork in water, if necessary, to prevent sticking).
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from pan to cooling rack.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: homemade snicker bars
directions: Line pan with foil; melt chocolate with oil and pour half of mixture into pan.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Set aside.
Spread chicken pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix 2 soups and milk; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with poultry seasoning.
Spread stuffing over top.
Bake in 325° oven 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Flatten each biscuit on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Use a lightly floured custard cup to flatten the biscuits.
Spread each biscuit with 1 heaping teaspoonful of the sauce.
Add meat, cheese and any other topping desired.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned and the cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: salami
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Mix everyday for next 3 days.
Fourth day, make into rolls.
Bake on broiler rack at 150° to 175° for 8 hours.

title: gamaretti di mare(main dish)
directions: Melt butter in skillet and stir in garlic, parsley, chives, brandy, cloves and nutmeg.
When bubbly, add shrimp, mushrooms, tomatoes and pepper.
Then saute until shrimp are cooked.
Transfer to heated platter.
Cook linguini or rice.

title: raised donuts
directions: Heat milk.
Put shortening, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add milk and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water. Add egg yolks, vanilla and yeast to milk mixture.
Stir in mashed potatoes and most of flour to form soft moist dough; knead well. Let rise until double (about 1/2 hour).
When raised, roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut donuts.
Let raise 1/2 hour.
Fry in deep fat at 350° until done.
Glaze while hot with 1 pound confectioners sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and enough hot water to make a thin paste.
Let cool.

title: mandarin pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in oil on both sides; remove from pan.
In skillet, add remaining ingredients except orange segments and green peppers.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add pork chops;
cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Add orange segments and green pepper, heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot pepper relish(serves 1)
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, catsup, oil, garlic and salt and boil 5 minutes.
Pack banana peppers in hot, sterilized jars tightly. Pour hot liquid over peppers and seal.

title: walnut balls
directions: In medium-size bowl, mix butter, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
If mixture is too soft to handle, chill and refrigerate for a few hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 300°
for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 30 minutes and shake 4 at a time in bag with confectioners sugar. Great for the holidays.

title: mama's chicken and dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together, using enough broth for desired thickness and moistness.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: sunset slush
directions: In blender; fill up 1/2 of blender with ice.
Add orange juice, banana and strawberries.
Turn on blender at highest setting until mixed.
If too thick, add more orange juice.
If not sweet enough, add sugar to taste.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix orange and pineapple juice along with enough hot water to dissolve jello. Add all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and serve cold.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Work into small ball in hand.
Place on greased cookie sheet, leaving space for expansion.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: lyn's company chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Cook soups, mayo, mushrooms, pimento and cheese.
Alternate noodles, asparagus and chicken.
Pour cooked sauce over the top.
Sprinkle cashews on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12. Easy and delicious!

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in big bowl.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator before serving.
With salad tongs, mix all together.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: bran bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let set 15 minutes.
Add honey, oil, salt and 3 cups flour.	Beat well.
Stir in bran flakes.
Add remaining flour and knead 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn once to grease top. Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down. Let rest 15 minutes. Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Add mayonnaise according to your own taste and mix well.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients;
mix well.
Add rice and raisins. Turn into baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: johnny manyetty
directions: Cook noodles, then brown ground beef.
Add onion and cook until done.
Cook celery and green pepper in water until done, then drain.
Mix altogether and add mushrooms, tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake in oven at 350°.
Takes about 30 minutes or until top is lightly brown.

title: green chili
directions: Brown pork in large stock pot and pour off fat. After pork is browned, add all ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.

More or less water can be used depending on how thick you want your chili. Can be served in bowl with crackers and shredded Cheddar cheese or rolled in flour tortillas in a cake pan. Top with Cheddar cheese and sour cream. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In blender, blend together jello and evaporated milk. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, sugar, strawberries, vanilla and Cool Whip; mixing well.
Pour into a one gallon freezer, adding enough sweet milk to fill container.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cut in Crisco.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Store in refrigerator about 3 to 4 hours.
Roll; let rise and bake at 400°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Shake flour, cayenne and chicken in a bag to coat.
Remove chicken and saute in margarine until lightly browned.
Remove chicken.
In same pan, add onions, garlic and grated ginger; fry until soft.
Add cumin and coriander; fry, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan; add cream and yogurt. Simmer for 30 minutes until sauce is brown and thick.
Serve over Rice Pilau.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 400° until golden brown (approximately 25 minutes).

title: peabody muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease muffin tins well.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder, and salt into a large bowl.
Add melted butter to egg and milk.
Beat to mix well; add vanilla. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Pour milk mixture into the bowl all at once.
Stir with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
CAUTION: DO NOT beat or overmix.
Quickly spoon batter into muffin tins, filling each slightly more than half full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes for a full size muffin pan.
Remove and serve hot.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large pot, melt margarine.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add flour, celery salt and pepper; blend.
Add salt, clam liquid with enough water added to make 2 cups and potatoes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add milk and clams and warm through.
Makes 6 servings.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: pound cake
directions: Milk, butter and Crisco should be room temperature.
Make a well in middle of dry ingredients.
Pour other ingredients into that well and beat all ingredients together for 20 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Do not preheat oven.)
Remove from oven and let sit for 15 minutes.
Remove from tube pan and let cool. Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: cool cucumber soup
directions: Combine broth, cucumbers and onion in a medium saucepan over low heat. Cook until cucumbers are just tender. Transfer to blender and blend with salt and pepper. Chill. When mixture is cool, combine with sour cream and yogurt. Serve in chilled cups or bowls and sprinkle with chopped cucumber and dill. Serves 4. Prep and cook time: 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage (room temperature), cheese and Bisquick until well blended. Use your hands.
Shape into small size balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: apache acorn soup
directions: Cover beef with water and bring to
boil in a heavy pot. Simmer until done; add salt and pepper as meat cooks tender. Remove beef and chop on a flat stone until split in shreds.
The meat broth continues to cook vigorously while meat and acorn flour (meal) are mixed together.
Apaches stress their food is always well done; no instant cooking.
Broth, meat and meal simmer together until the broth bubbles creamy white with yellow flecks, pleasantly acorn scented and flavored.

title: ruby cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls or
drop off of teaspoon.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 17 to 18 minutes.
Cool on pan.
Will be pale and soft until cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix well graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Keep out 1 cup of mixture.
Pat remaining crumbs in a large pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, then layer alternately cherries and Cool Whip, 2 layers each.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: international bean dip
directions: If using dried beans, soak beans.
Boil in 2 quarts of water for 1 minute and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Boil 45 minutes until tender in3 quarts and 4 cups water on high.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Lower heat and simmer 45 more minutes or until done.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Blend in mayonnaise. Form into a flat mound on serving dish and top with preserves. Garnish with raspberries.
Serve with wafers and crackers of your choice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and cream cheese in a bowl.
Add contents and Cool Whip to graham cracker crust and top with syrup. Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: banana fritters
directions: Beat together egg and milk until foamy.
Add Bisquick and blend until smooth.
Cut banana into twenty pieces and fold carefully into batter.
Drop each piece of banana, now coated with batter, onto medium-hot griddle sprayed with Pam.
Cook like pancakes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend biscuit mix with butter.
Stir in butter and milk; mix to make a soft dough.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and beat until lemon-colored.
Whip cream until the consistency of mayonnaise.
Add cream alternately with powdered milk to the butter mixture.
Drain pineapple very well, then add to the butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Line Pyrex with ladyfingers.
Cover with cream mixture.
Repeat procedure until cream is finished.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot milk.
Chop fine the nuts, cherries, pineapple and dates.
Crush crackers fine.
Combine all these ingredients and mix well.
Pour hot milk over all and mix well. Pack firm into tube pan or baking pan.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: crescent turkey squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well. Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of meat mixture, twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved butter.
If you like, sprinkle with crushed seasoned croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Melt white chocolate on Defrost in microwave.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread into a greased pan.
Chill before cutting into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a large bowl mix corn meal, beaten egg, buttermilk, chopped onion and mayonnaise.
Spoon drop into hot oil.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend all liquid ingredients.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Knead dough with hands.
Dough should be stiff, but if too dry, add more liquid.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Keep in oven overnight to really dry out hard.

title: earthquake dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan (if you use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, this will run over in your oven).
Cover bottom of pan with coconut.
Sprinkle nuts over coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over nuts.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake mix; do not try to spread.
Bake cake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: luby's date nut muffins(moist and delicious!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Set aside to cool.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add the egg and beat lightly. Then add vanilla, flour and pecans, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add cooled dates, water and baking soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into muffin pans which have been sprayed with Pam, greased or lined with paper cupcake liners.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Don't overbake.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place ham on top of breast and cheese and then roll.
Mix in bowl the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and Good Seasons mix.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining evaporated milk (1/4 cup), cake mix and margarine.
Mix well.
Press half of the cake mixture onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and 1/4 cup walnuts over crust; drizzle with caramel mixture. Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel mixture. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Chill.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks, milk and lime juice with wire whisk.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: "raisin bread"
directions: In large pot, prepare milk, margarine, shortening, salt, vanilla and whiskey.
Add yeast to mixture.
Follow yeast instructions regarding the water amount.
Mix gently.
Add eggs, sugar and raisins.
Gradually add flour (if needed, add more flour as you don't want the dough too liquidy).
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise until double in size.

title: tortilla chicken casserole
directions: Mix chiles, onions, garlic, sour cream, soups and chicken well. Grease a 13x9x2-inch dish.
Preheat the oven to 325°.
Put half of the tortillas, cut in bite sized pieces in the bottom of the casserole.
Layer with half of the soup mixture, then half of the cheese.
Repeat layers (cheese will be on top).

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt butter in large containers.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Roll in walnut size balls and place on waxed paper.
(Put into freezer about 1 hour.) Melt 1/2 block of paraffin wax in top of double boiler, then add 1 (6 ounce) package of chocolate morsels to double boiler.
Then dip balls to coat in chocolate.
(Be careful not to get wax too hot.)

title: open-faced eggplant
directions: Fry eggplant and peppers with garlic in oil 15 minutes.
Cut bread lengthwise and divide the eggplant mixture, tomato and escarole between each half of bread.

title: potato crunch casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and pour over thawed potatoes.
Set aside.
Mix together sour cream, soup, onion, seasoning and cheese.
Add to hash browns and mix thoroughly.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and food coloring (optional).
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Put mixture into 9-inch pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving. Top with your favorite fruit (fresh or canned topping).

title: seven-up cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon in color.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Mix well for 3 to 4 minutes.
Place in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mix all together well; chill 4 to 6 hours.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil; cook fast.
Turn once.
Place in brown paper bag with paper towels (keeps them warm).
Serve with fried chicken or finger foods.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Combine beef and onion; cook until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain.
Add beans and next 4 ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Fry venison in peanut oil until brown.
Add water chestnuts and pineapple, then stir in cream of broccoli soup until smooth. Add soy sauce to season.
Add frozen stir-fry vegetables.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Layer 1 can of biscuits; cut biscuits in 1/4 pieces.
Roll in melted margarine; place in tube pan.
Add a layer of onion, peppers, bacon and cheese.
Add second can of biscuits and another layer of vegetables.
Do the same thing with third can of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: This makes a small pie.
For a 9-inch pie, use more ingredients (about 1 1/2 times more).
Combine the sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, water, eggs and butter in blender bowl and blend for 1/2 minute.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Test with knife in center as you would pumpkin pie.

title: crispy meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 9 ingredients. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Shape into 1-1/2 inch balls and place in a greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink. Yields 16 meatballs.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn and keep warm.
Cook first 4 ingredients until sugar melts.
Keep cooking, without stirring, until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water (270°).
Add vanilla and butter extracts.
Pour syrup over popped corn.
Coat pan with oleo and form balls.

title: tater soup
directions: Cube potatoes; add onions and cook until soft.
When soft, drain liquid.
Mix sour cream and soups together and add to potatoes.
Let simmer about 10 minutes.

title: english coffee cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat well.
Mix in flour.
Spread cookie dough evenly over greased
cookie sheet (approximately 12 x 14-inch). Brush beaten egg whites over top of dough and sprinkle over chopped nuts.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Cut when warm.
Enjoy!

title: key lime pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add the sweetened condensed milk and the lime peel.
Gradually add the lime juice, beating at medium speed until mixed.
Turn mixture into baked pastry shell.
Cover and chill 4 hours.
Before serving, top with whipped cream and garnish with lime slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Brush on tortillas.
Cut.
Put on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake in a 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls appetizers
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.
Allow to reach room temperature before baking or can be completely baked, frozen and then reheated in micro.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery, cashews and onions; toss lightly.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of noodles on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients until combined. Shape level tablespoon into ball. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from sheet.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 60 calories each.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Chill and serve.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Make into balls the size of a large marble.
Place
on
slightly
greased
cookie
sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are slightly brown.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put bite sized pieces of chicken into a greased casserole dish. Mix together mushroom soup and milk and pour over chicken. Melt margarine and add chicken broth. Mix with dressing mix and put on top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: pineapple glazed ham balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into balls. Chill.
In large frypan lightly brown ham balls in the shortening. In a bowl combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly. Pour over ham balls.
Cover with lid.
Cook on medium for about 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add onion, parsley, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix together.
Let set for awhile.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add the milk and asparagus juice together and mix with mushroom soup.
Place layer of cracker crumbs, then layer of asparagus tips.
Do this about 3 times until all asparagus is used.
Add the mushroom soup mixture over the top of the asparagus and cracker crumbs.
Add grated cheese to top and bake until bubbly and looks done. (350° oven for 20 - 30 minutes)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add ground beef.
Cook till done. Add onion salt, pepper, and macaroni to the meat.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with slices of cheddar cheese.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese. Mix all ingredients well. Roll into balls the size of a quarter and bake on a large cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until brown). Place in a bowl lined with paper towels to absorb some of the grease.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with Dijon mustard.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Stuff peppers and bake until a light brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes; cook slowly
in
2 cups of water.
Cover pot. When tender, drain;
let cool just until you can handle. Skin and mash.
Add
all
other
ingredients; beat well.
When blended, pile into a 1
quart
casserole;
dot top with a little butter and about
a dozen miniature marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until marshmallows are brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk; cool slightly.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine salt, sugar, egg and oil with yeast and water.
Add milk and flour in 3 parts; mix well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead slightly until smooth.
Put into buttered bowl; butter top. Cover with clean dish cloth.
Let rise to double.
Take out desired amount.
Knead, roll and cut to desired shapes.
Put into buttered pan; butter tops.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Put remaining dough in buttered, covered Tupperware bowl.
Refrigerate; use as needed.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash and onion mixture with salt and pepper.
Add egg.
Combine in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto hot greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Parboil veggies, then pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and soup and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate popovers
directions: Position rack in lower third of oven.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 6-c. popover pan or 6 (6 oz.) custard cups.
Set custard cups in jelly roll pan.
Sift flour, granulated sugar, cocoa and salt into medium bowl; set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute.
Beat in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 minutes.
Immediately remove popovers to wire rack.
Generously sprinkle powdered sugar over popovers. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 popovers.

title: caesar salad
directions: Whisk together the first 8 ingredients.
Stir in freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Place thoroughly dried lettuce in a large bowl (tear leaves horizontally across spine) and toss with the dressing.
Season generously with pepper; garnish with croutons and sprinkle with additional grated Parmesan cheese on top.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together cornbread, onion, celery, garlic, bread, oleo and eggs.
Pour in broth until it is the consistency you want.
(Some people like their dressing dry, others soupy.)
Add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and sage to taste.
Add meat if you like and cook about 30 minutes at 350°.
If you don't have enough broth, you can use a can of cream of chicken soup.
This can be made with chicken, turkey or pork.

title: vienna sausage gravy
directions: Open Viennas.
Drain and save juice.
Mash up Viennas.
Pour shortening in pan.
Heat.
Add Viennas and flour.
Mix juice with equal amount water.
When flour mixture is brown, add water and juice mixture.
Remove from heat when it thickens.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: egg custard
directions: Bake pie shell for 5 minutes at 450°; set aside.
Warm 2 cups milk.
Blend in other ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cut oven temperature down to 350° and continue baking until done.
Baking time is approximately 35 minutes.

title: crumpets
directions: Combine sugar and yeast in small bowl.
Stir in warm water. Let set until yeast begins to foam, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Place sliced apple in greased square pan 8 x 8 x 2 or a baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and the topping is golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix carrot, onion, pimento, sour cream and soup in large bowl. Add drained parboiled squash, salt and pepper to taste. Pour into large casserole. Toss dressing in stick of butter and spread on top of mixture.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: supper strata
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and bread.
Place 4 slices of bread in pan.
Place cheese on bread slices and cover with 1/2 of mixture.
Place remaining bread on others and top with remaining cheese.
Cover with rest of mixture.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let rest for 10 minutes before serving.

title: frango mints
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
In bowl, mix margarine, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Add melted chocolate chips and peppermint to mixture.
Beat well.
Drop by small globs on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper and chill.

title: new england pumpkin pie filling
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, milk and salt. Add this to a small amount of pumpkin. Blend the ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon into the rest of the pumpkin. Combine the two mixtures. Pour into your favorite pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes. Test the center with a clean table knife. Remove from oven when the knife comes out clean. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Bring the cream or milk to a boil.
Remove from heat; add shortening, sugar, soda and salt and mix well.
Cool to lukewarm and add egg and yeast (dissolved in a little warm water).
Stir the mix into the flour and knead the dough a little.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Roll and spread with melted butter; sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll in a long roll and slice.
Put rolls in cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, ice with favorite icing.

title: blueberry cream pie(summer pie; cool)
directions: Blend together milk and lemon juice.
Fold in coarsely chopped blueberries.
Pour into the baked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with whole blueberries and refrigerate.
Quick and good.

title: lawry's mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until crumbly.
Drain.
Add seasoned salt, taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chiles.
Blend well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, approximately 10 minutes.
Combine Ricotta cheese and eggs.
In bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, put 1/2 meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 tortillas.
Spread 1/2 cheese mixture on top.
Then 1/2 Jack cheese.
Repeat once.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put layer of chops in a baking dish, then add a layer of thick sliced onions, then a layer of thick sliced potatoes.
Repeat until ingredients are used up.
Add 1/2 can of water to the mushroom soup and mix well.
Pour over casserole. Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix soups
together; mix meat and wine with soup.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours and serve over rice.

title: soft white bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 5 cups flour, sugar, dry milk powder, yeast and salt.

title: lime cottage ring
directions: Dissolve the package of lime gelatin in cup of boiling water. Chill until partially set.
Blend in the cup of mayonnaise or salad dressing, then fold in the cup of finely chopped celery, cup of finely diced green peppers and cup of large curd cottage cheese.

title: easy beef soup
directions: Mix broth, water and beets in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend flour and sour cream.
Pour some hot soup into cream to warm.
Pour into soup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over boiled potatoes or noodles, if desired.
Or just serve with bread and butter.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the above together.
Put into a 10-inch pie plate and make a crust.
Bake for 5 minutes at 375°.

title: santa fe soup
directions: DO NOT DRAIN JUICES.
