Brown hamburger meat with either chopped onion or dry beefy onion soup mix.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add juice in cans.
Get soup good and hot to boiling, then you can simmer for about 30 minutes to an hour. Stir occasionally.
Can top with sour cream and/or shredded cheese.
Serve with Hot Cornbread.

title: crab mold
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Add to soup and heat but do not boil.
Let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to soup mixture.
Pour in greased mold and refrigerate 6 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 12.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Flake into small pieces. Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Water chestnuts may be used instead of pecans.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine melted chocolate and margarine in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients (except nuts).
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine ingredients and finish filling 1 gallon jar with water.
Chill overnight.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside. Brown meat, onion and green pepper in butter or margarine. Transfer to a casserole dish and thoroughly mix all ingredients. Add macaroni and mix well. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°, covered, for 2 hours or until bubbly.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies(no bake cookies)
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Add oats.
Stir to mix well.
Quickly drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper or foil.
Cool completely.
Store in cool, dry place.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°.

title: weight watchers chocolate mousse
directions: Blend cold water and gelatine in blender 1 minute.
Add shake mix, sweetener, milk and water.
Blend 1 minute, adding the ice cubes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use egg whites for meringue.
Take out of oven when it is still a little shaky.

title: soft never fail sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in shortening, add milk, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll on lightly floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Arrange on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven.

title: tomato spice cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Generously grease and flour 2 round layer pans, 8 or 9-inch or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan. Measure dry ingredients into large
bowl.
Add soup and shortening.
Beat at low to medium speed for 2 minutes, 300 strokes with a spoon, scraping sides
and
bottom
of bowl constantly. Add
eggs
and water.
Beat
minutes
more,
scraping
bowl frequently.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand in pans 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool.
Frost
with
cream cheese frosting.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in vegetable oil until soft.
Add 2 Tbsp. flour, chili powder and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add water and instant beef broth and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add in cheddar cheese.

title: greek dressing
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, then add cheese.

title: corn flakes surprise muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine corn flakes and milk. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cereal is softened. Add egg and oil. Beat well. Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Portion evenly into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray. Make a deep indentation in top of batter of each muffin. Fill each with measuring teaspoonful of preserves or jam. Bake at 400° about 18 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with soft cream cheese, if desired. Makes 12 muffins.

title: crusty honey whole wheat bread
directions: Heat milk, water and honey to 120°.
Assemble doughmaker.
In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 cup
whole wheat flour, yeast, egg, salt and warm milk mixture.
Mix at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups whole wheat flour and 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour and continue kneading 3 more minutes.
If dough is sticky, knead in enough of remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled. Punch down and divide into 2 equal parts.
Shape into loaves and place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: gumdrop refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg, rind, vanilla and water.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, gumdrops and nuts.
Shape into a roll, wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: corned beef loaf
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat peas and liquid; add to gelatin.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, celery, green pepper and onion together and add mayonnaise, milk, salt, vinegar and Tabasco. Then add to peas and gelatin mixture; mix well and add corned beef.
Put into dish or pan lined with waxed paper.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce as main dish.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp and scallop scampi with broccoli over linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Steam broccoli for about 3 minutes and set aside.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Over low heat, add softened cream cheese.
Press 1 can of crescent rolls into bottom of glass dish. Pour in meat mixture.
Use other can for top crust.
(Works best if you press into waxed paper before putting on top of sausage.) Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is light brown.
Enjoy!

title: simple baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bean pot or a Pyrex dish. Place 3 or 4 strips of bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Marinate shrimp, onions, celery, salt and lemon pepper in Italian dressing.

title: fig cake
directions: Preheat the
oven
to
Grease
and
flour
a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat the eggs in a large mixing bowl, then beat in the sugar and salt.
Add the oil and beat again.

title: catalina taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add onion and chili powder.
Cook until tender; drain and cool.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, green onions, beans and cheese.
Mix and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with sugar.
Slowly add milk to make creamy.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Mix using an electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill before serving.

title: spicy bars
directions: Bring raisins and water to boil.
Add oil and cool.
Add egg and sugar.
Mix together all remaining ingredients.
Add.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 baking dish at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars and dust with powdered sugar.

title: pickle barrel dills
directions: Bring water to boil and dissolve salt in it.
Let water cool. In bottom of large wide mouth 5 gallon crock, jar or jug, place dill, spices and garlic.
(A 1 gallon jar will hold about 15 pickles.)
Pack cucumbers into scalded container and pour brine over them.
Place a plate over the jar to keep pickles from floating.
Stored at about 85°, pickles will be at the new stage in about 1 week, at half sour to sour stage in about 2 weeks to 20 days.
At colder temps, curing will take longer.
These are like the old fashioned "General Store" barrel pickles.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine and store in a tightly covered jar.
For one serving, place one rounded teaspoon in a cup.
Add boiling water.
Add a cinnamon stick for more flavor and eye appeal.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil and add onion, pepper, beef and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, cumin, cayenne pepper, chili powder, oregano and salt. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
(If mixture is too thick, add water.)
Stir in the beans and cover and simmer for 5 minutes, until the beans are heated.
Add half of the juice from the beans while cooking.

title: congealed potato salad
directions: Heat milk and gelatin until dissolved.
In a large bowl, combine other ingredients.
Add milk mixture.
Spray a 12-cup Bundt pan with Pam.
Press mixture firmly in the Bundt pan.
Cover and refrigerate until set.
Unmold on serving dish and slice when ready to serve.
Garnish with fresh parsley before slicing.

title: layered cherry cake
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spread the cherry pie filling evenly in pan.
Spread pineapple over pie filling and sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Thinly slice margarine and place over nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: carrot raisin salad(servings:  7)
directions: Toss carrots lightly with raisins.
Blend remaining ingredients and stir into carrot mixture.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: chili relleno souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add cheese and mix well.
Batter will be very runny.
Bake in a well-greased casserole at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place raw meat in casserole.
Season with Accent and seasoned salt.
Add vegetables.
Pour undiluted soup over all.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Top stew with one can heated and drained onions, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ranch style chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces. Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine. Mix mushroom soup, celery soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add chicken and vegetables. Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese in baking dish, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Very good!!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
margarine.
Sift
plain flour (I use White Lily) and fill sugar box.
Alternate flour and eggs, one at a time.
Beat
well after each.
Blend in flavor.
Bake in well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue for a bunch
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soups, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Simmer.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil all ingredients for approximately 5 minutes and then pour into a wide mouth jar or container and add hard-boiled eggs (peeled).
Let set overnight.
Will keep for weeks.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cook bacon slightly; add onion, leeks, carrots, turnips, cabbage, celery and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes or until soft, not browned.
Add soup stock and seasonings; boil gently about 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add peas and macaroni and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until all vegetables and macaroni are tender.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans and parsley. Cook 1/2 hour or until beans are tender.
Just before serving, add grated cheese; stir over heat until cheese is melted.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease off.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes, simmer for a few minutes.
Cook noodles by directions.
Layer sauce, cheeses and then single layer of noodles, about 4 across.
Use a cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Layer all this ending with cheeses.
Cook 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and light brown at 375°.

title: 3-c cake(chocolate cream cheese cake)
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted margarine together by hand. Mixture will be stiff.
Pat into a very lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma's crumb cake(serves 8)
directions: When ready for oven, sprinkle crumbs on top.
Add another 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender and light brown.
Combine egg and milk; add to mix and stir only until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and poppy seed.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chilled red pepper soup
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir peppers, onion and garlic until tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in broth, thyme and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed and vegetables are soft.
In food processor bowl with metal blade (or blender container), combine pepper mixture with half and half; process until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours or until thoroughly chilled.
If desired, serve with additional half and half.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: beefy burritos
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, cumin, jalapenos and tomatoes for about 10 minutes.
Cook the diced potatoes in water for about 12 to 15 minutes, then add to the meat for another 5 minutes.
Serve on the tortillas with shredded Cheddar cheese and lettuce.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Mix everything and shape in loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove and pour off fat.

title: quick vegetable casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo.
Mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Spread on top of vegetable casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a bowl. Add 2 whole eggs and 2 egg yolks.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla.
Spread topping on batter and bake at 325° until done. Cut into squares and remove while warm.

title: grandmaw's chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Blend in oats, flour and water to make fairly stiff dough.
Blend in pecans, raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are just browned around edges and feel firm in center.
Don't overbake.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on rack. Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar. Add eggs.
Mix well with drained fruit and bread.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Dress with mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook in deep fryer until desired darkness

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Crush Doritos.
Place half of crushed Doritos in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over crushed Doritos.
Then another layer of Doritos. Then rest of mixture.
Top with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese
stand at room temperature until soft. Mix all of cream cheese
with
chopped onion and 2 packages of beef which has been chopped
very small.
Mix real well.
Form into 2 small balls or
one
large
ball.
Roll
balls in third package of beef which has also been chopped very small.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave vanilla cream pudding(4 servings)
directions: Place milk in 2-cup size glass container to heat level 8 for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine jello, cold water and boiling water.
Chill until it starts to thicken.
Mix remaining ingredients with electric mixer or by hand.
Put back in refrigerator to mold and chill.

title: pecan balls
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans. Form into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into the bottom of a casserole dish. Pour can of chili on top of cream cheese and spread.
Mix the two cheeses together and sprinkle on top of chili (use all of cheese) and place in microwave for 5 minutes, until melted.
Serve with chips.

title: marlene's punch
directions: Bring to a boil the water and sugar.
Cool and add the juices and bananas.
Freeze.
Makes 3 quarts.
Add orange pop and serve as slush.

title: eula's pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar.
Then add syrup and salt.
Add butter and vanilla flavoring.
Add chopped pecans to mixture and stir.
Pour into Pet Ritz regular (not deep dish) pie shell and bake at 350° in a preheated oven for approximately 40-45 Minutes. Pie is done when it is slightly firm in the middle.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve, use 2 heaping tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put milk in freezer to chill, then whip.
Add lemon juice and sugar, then the jello and cheese mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: olive and pepper pizza(low-fat; 6 grams)
directions: In heated oil, saute the peppers until soft, but not limp. Remove skillet from the heat and stir in olives, salt, pepper and basil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the saute on the pita rounds and top with Mozzarella.
Bake on a cookie sheet until the cheese is bubbly and golden in color.

title: candy orange slice cake
directions: Cut into small pieces the orange slices, dates and pecans. Sift flour (2 cups) over mixture.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Sift remaining flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Mix all together thoroughly.
Bake in a 300° oven.
Bake an angel food cake pan for 20 to 22 minutes.
Bake loaf pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes (use 2 loaf pans or 1 angel food cake pan).
Bake cupcakes 1 hour and 15 minutes (makes about 48 cupcakes).

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
Spread 1/2 cup walnuts evenly on bottom of pan; set aside.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice and 1/2 cup water in greased casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion mix over chicken.
Mix chicken soup and water.
Pour over
casserole.
Cover
with
foil
and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: new year's cookies
directions: Work dough like bread.
Let rise.
Fry by teaspoon in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Powder with sugar.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Blend in vanilla.
Blend in half of sugar.
Add remaining sugar alternately with milk using enough sugar to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Frost cookies when cool.

title: fabulous baked fish
directions: Rinse fillets; pat dry and set aside.
In small bowl, combine crumbs, cheese and garlic powder.
Dip fillets in egg whites, then into crumb mix.
Coat well.
Arrange fillets in a shallow microproof baking dish with the thickest parts facing outside of dish.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook cycle for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: my boursin cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients (may be done in a food processor with steel blade) and blend thoroughly.
Shape into a ball and roll in crushed pepper.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Boursin cheese may be frozen.

title: greek vegetables
directions: Chop zucchini, eggplant and onion and saute in oil and butter. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low until tender.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Cool sweet potatoes and drain.
Cream with sugar, butter and vanilla.
Make thick.
Roll around marshmallow and roll in coconut. Bake until brown.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix together in a double boiler the marshmallows, sugar and milk.
Stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture is gooey. Cool. Crush the graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Place in a large bowl and add nuts and fruits.
When the marshmallow mixture has cooled, pour over the ingredients in the bowl.
Mix and put in Pyrex dishes.
Put in refrigerator.

title: hot dog fritters
directions: Heat fat in deep fryer or skillet to 375°.
Cook the hot dogs in water about 4 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Slice each hot dog in 6 pieces. Combine meal, flour, onion, egg, and milk.
Stir in hot dog pieces.
Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except yogurt, until smooth.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover and chill.
Serve as a dip with a variety of raw vegetables. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until mixture thickens.
Beat eggs well. Add hot syrup slowly, beating constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a moderate oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in 15 pieces.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Cover with greased wax paper. Let sit out overnight or 6 to 8 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet. Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.
Fry a few at a time, about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients, then add milk and peaches.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cooking dish.
Pour in other ingredients.
Cook until golden brown and bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole with oleo.
Melt stick of oleo in pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain peas and asparagus.
Put asparagus on top of peas; add soup and water chestnuts which have been drained.
Top with shredded cheese, then bread crumbs made from whole wheat bread.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: ernie wittler's elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces with chainsaw (allow about 2 weeks cutting time).
Reserve the trunk (to store the pieces in).
Make enough brown gravy to cover meat.
Cook over 465° kerosene fire about 4 weeks.
Serves 9,500 people.
If more guests are expected, the two rabbits may be added.
Do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: chicken eden isle
directions: Line bottom of casserole with dried beef slices.
Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Salt and pepper.
Mix together the mushrooms, soups and cream cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over white or wild rice.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add corn syrup, sugar, salt, vanilla and melted butter, mixing together very well.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell, then pour prepared mixture over nuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then decrease to 350° for 30 minutes.
Or bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until silver knife inserted in center comes clean.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Heat oil to medium, about 1 inch deep in frying pan.
Put about 1/2 cup of potato mixture in oil, forming a pancake.
Cook until brown; turn and cook until light brown on second side.
Remove and drain on a paper towel.
Serve with sausage, applesauce and pancake syrup.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all together and add to pie shell. Chill.

title: nine layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order given and do not toss. Spread salad dressing over layered mixture. Sprinkle sugar over dressing and top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with hard cooked eggs and tomato wedges before serving.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets and set aside.
Add vinegar to beet juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Add sugar and cloves.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cloves and pour hot liquid over jello and stir until dissolved.
Add beets to jello and refrigerate until set. Serve with cottage cheese or sour cream (optional).

title: unbeatables(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, baking powder and egg whites.
Add walnuts and apricots; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: chicken-rosemary casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator (6 to 8 hours).
Mix and spoon into deep 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours in 375° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.
Delicious served with rolls and salad.

title: cherry pizza
directions: In a 10-inch pie plate, buttered, add pie filling and cake mix.
Spread cake mix on dry.
Slice margarine on top.
Add pecans, if desired.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven. Delicious!

title: granny's apple cake
directions: Stir up filling ingredients and set aside.

title: potato and carrot pudding
directions: Mix
vegetables.
Add	to
dry
ingredients.
Makes
3 (2-pound) cans.
Serves 60.
Put in 2-pound coffee cans; leave lid off.
Cook
in
a water bath for 1 hour.
Cool on a rack, then store in a cool place, or freeze for longer life.
Serve with a hard sauce.

title: egg rolls
directions: Combine the pork, salt, pepper and vinegar. Then add garlic and onion, then carrots and other vegetables. Mix in egg and then cornstarch. Wrap this mixture in egg roll wrappers and fry in vegetable oil until pork is done (5 minutes).

title: pie crust(never fail)
directions: Cut Crisco, flour and salt.
Add beaten egg, water and vinegar; blend thoroughly.
Bake as recipe says.
Yields 3 large crusts.
Roll between waxed paper.

title: norwegian crowns
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Mix well.
Add egg, almond extract and flour and mix thoroughly.
Fill cookie press half full.
Form crowns on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat the pineapple with juice to boiling. Add the Jell-O.
Mix well and cool.
Add the buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until congealed.
Delicious!

title: heavenly devil's food cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: corn bread dressing(100 servings)
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper until clear but not brown; remove from heat.
Add bread, corn bread and seasonings to the sauteed vegetables; toss lightly to mix.
Add stock to dry ingredients; mix together lightly.
Place an equal quantity into each greased roasting pan (18 x 26-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 100 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: carlie's boiled raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in the water for 5 minutes; cool.
Add soda to raisins.
Add raisins and water to other ingredients.
Bake at 325° until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
"Makes a bunch!"

title: biscotti(italian anise toast cookies)
directions: Combine sugar, oil and milk.
Mix well.
Add eggs and flavorings; mix well.
Add nuts, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Divide dough.
On floured surface, roll each part into sticks about 14-inches long and size of broomstick.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and slice each roll into pieces at an angle 1/2-inch thick.
Return to pan, cut side down, and rebake at 425° until brown.
Cool.
This makes a large quantity.
They can be stored in tightly closed tin for 4 to 5 months.

title: baked parmesan fish
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
I put mine in a Ziploc to mix.
In a bowl, beat egg and milk.
Dip fillets in egg mixture, then coat with cheese mixture. Arrange in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until flaky.

title: orange flip (energy drink)
directions: Blend ingredients in a blender for 40 to 90 seconds until well beaten. Good for breakfast or as a pick-me-up between meals.

title: vegetable spaghetti
directions: Fry any choice of fresh vegetables in pan with a tablespoon of oil or diet oleo.
Add garlic to frypan.
When the vegetables are browned, about 5 minutes, pour over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over and optional Italian dressing; add parsley. Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4.

title: christmas sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form two rolls and wrap individually in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Place oats in bowl, pour boiling water over it; add 1/4 cup brown sugar and milk.
When mixture is only warm, crumble in yeast.
Sift and measure 2 cups flour, add and beat smooth.
Let stand in a warm place until light and bubbly.
Stir in salt, melted margarine and other 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Sift, measure and add 3 1/2 to 4 cups flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cover closely or grease top.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Punch down.
When light again, form into loaves.
Place in well-greased pans.
Brush tops with egg white (beaten slightly) and sprinkle quick oats over loaves.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans at once.

title: walnut bread
directions: Add flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, shortening, milk and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist; add nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 350° until done.

title: pad thaismall width noodles
directions: Soak the noodles in cold water overnight or 15 minutes in hot water.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Chop scallion and cilantro. Grind or crush the peanuts.

Preheat the oil in the WOK on medium-high, then add garlic and shrimp then stir until the shrimp turns white, add the egg and stir till cooked, add the noodles and all of the seasonings, stir or toss well.
Turn heat off, add bean sprouts and scallions.
Serves 4.

title: pistou(french version of pesto sauce)
directions: In a food processor, combine basil, garlic and nuts.
Process until finely chopped.
Add oil, if necessary.
Transfer to a bowl and thoroughly stir in the oil and cheese to form a creamy sauce with the consistency of thick gravy.
Serve over pasta or as a dip.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Place bacon in bottom of long casserole dish. Place uncooked rice on bacon. Mix soup with water and sprinkle evenly over rice; lightly sprinkle oregano and garlic powder over rice. Cut up chicken and remove skin; season with Tony's seasoning, garlic powder and oregano; lay on rice. Pour soup and water mixture over chicken; sprinkle with paprika. Seal tightly with foil; bake at 300° for 2 hours. Do Not Peek!

title: coca cola cake
directions: Blend flour and sugar in mixing bowl. In a sauce pan bring cola, cocoa and butter to a boil. Mix buttermilk, soda, eggs, and vanilla; add to the flour mixture. Add cocoa mixture and marshmallows. This batter will be thin. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: beans, peas and rice
directions: Mix peas and beans in a jar for storage.
Put a scoop of mixed peas and beans in a large pan of water and soak an hour or overnight.
Rinse and add more water, chopped onion, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Cook slowly on stove top or in a crock-pot. In another pan, boil a cup of rice.
Mix cooked rice with cooked beans.
This is a delicious way to stretch your budget.
You can feed an army for pennies.

title: holiday pumpkin cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Add one can of pumpkin.
Cook in a bundt pan following directions on the cake package.
Drizzle with a vanilla glaze.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix and set aside flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Beat eggs and add buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and mix well, then add prunes and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: oven chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bag.
Melt butter in pan.
Shake chicken in bag with dry ingredients.
Put chicken in pan skin side up.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: mexican magic
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain fat and add taco seasoning according to package.
Add Ro-Tel, beans and soup.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend cheese and tomatoes in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve warm as dip with corn chips or crackers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: "unfried" chicken
directions: Place ice water in large bowl and soak chicken parts while preparing the breading.
Spray baking sheet with Pam.

title: tomato, onions and peppers
directions: *As many as you want, according to how big a dish you need.

title: pound cake
directions: Dump all ingredients together and beat until smooth and well blended.
Cook in a 250° to 300° oven in a tube pan for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: If using fresh sprouts, rinse well and cut off any discolored leaves.
With a paring knife, cut a "plus"
sign in the stem end to insure even cooking.
Place the sprouts in a large saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling for about 10 minutes or until the stem side is tender when pierced with a knife.
Drain and set the sprouts aside.

title: green chile o'
directions: Line bottom of greased glass dish (8 x 10 x 2-inch) with green chiles.
Pile Longhorn cheese on top.
Beat eggs with 3 tablespoons water and pour over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve on square crackers, such as Triscuits.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.

title: catalina chicken(low-fat)
directions: Cook dressing, onion soup mix and cranberry sauce until well blended.
Pour over chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Bake until chicken is tender.

title: railroad slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar and onion on cabbage.
Heat vinegar and spices and oil. Pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate.
Chill this and it tastes just as good tomorrow as today.

title: hitchcock chili
directions: Brown meat in large pot; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 30 minutes.
May prefer to place in crock-pot and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: sweet and spicy glazed chicken(cook in crock-pot)
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in crock-pot.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except cornstarch and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high:
3 to 4 hours).
When done, remove chicken breasts and turn crock-pot to high.
Cover!
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into liquid in crock-pot.
Place cover slightly ajar on crock-pot.
Cook until thickened, about 15 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is thick and ivory colored. Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Gradually fold in flour mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ape cake
directions: Add lard or Crisco; mix as for pie dough.
Add sour milk and baking soda.
If too moist, add more flour.
Bake at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients; form balls and roll in coconut.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and refrigerate. Serves 6 to 8.

title: one pot stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add beef and brown. Drain.
Stir in mushrooms, lemon juice, consomme, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in noodles.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Before serving, mix in sour cream and heat.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix beef, onions and celery; cook until tender.
Add cooked noodles, tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Put in pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix and pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake for 5 minutes at 475°.
Turn back to 425° and bake for 10 minutes more or until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: cabbage salad
directions: For dressing, combine and
whisk together the sugar, olive oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and 1/2 of the package of the chicken seasoning from the Ramen soup.

title: simply almond shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter, sugar, 1 cup of the almonds and almond extract in bowl and beat with mixer until blended.
Add flour and beat until well blended.
Spoon dough into ungreased baking pan; press dough evenly into pan and sprinkle with remaining almonds and press them lightly into the dough. Bake about 25 minutes.
Immediately use butter knife to cut shortbread into 15 squares.
Then cut each square diagonally.
Let cool.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: barbecue marinate for roasts
directions: Marinate roast several hours or overnight.
Grill or bake.

title: meme's banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour 1/2 of batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together, except potato chips and place in a 2 1/2- quart casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove one hour before baking.
Sprinkle potato chips over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: beef shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in skillet. Saute beef and onion until onion is transparent. Stir in salt and pepper.
Place meat mixture in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Spread potatoes on top and top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: okra-bacon casserole
directions: Slice okra into thin rounds.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Place layers of okra, tomatoes, salt, pepper, onion and sweet pepper.
Repeat layers.
Lay bacon on top overlapping each pieces. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no egg chocolates chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Add chips and nuts.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix all the above and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup brown sugar, then 3/4 cup coconut, then 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fruit fondue
directions: Clean strawberries or other fruit and arrange on a platter. Combine sugar, butter and light cream in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat. Add rum after sauce sits 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Provide sauce for dipping the fruit.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice.
Add celery and walnuts.
Cover and chill.
Mix mayonnaise and honey together until smooth.
Add to apple mixture and toss.
Serve on lettuce.
Raisins are good in it too!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini. Sift together, flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix well and add nuts and raisins. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put beef in blender and chop.
Mix cream cheese and rest of ingredients.
Form into a ball and chill.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix everything together except milk.
Beat for 10 minutes. Add milk.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields one large pie.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Combine milk with cheese, onion, salt, mustard and egg.
Add mushrooms.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set firm.
While mushrooms are baking, prepare spinach according to package directions.
Drain well.
Before serving, arrange spinach around the edge of mushroom dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Mix cheese cake mix and milk according to box direction then fold this into the cream cheese mixture along with 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Put filling into pie crust (you may need an extra crust).
Put strawberry pie filling on top and the rest of the Cool Whip.

title: tenderloin kabobs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Place steaks in glass or ceramic casserole dish.
Add marinade; cover and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning at least twice.
Broil about 4 inches away from heat source 6 to 8 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together the jello and boiling water and allow to cool. Add the pineapple, pie filling and nuts to the jello and water. Refrigerate to set.
Beat the remaining ingredients smooth. Top jello mixture.
Makes 18 servings.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook noodles as package directs; drain. Place sausages in shallow baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes, turning once.
Lower heat to 350°.
Combine sausage drippings and noodles. Arrange 1/2 noodles in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with combined applesauce, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Cover with rest of noodles; top with sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot.

title: easy sausage pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Mix Bisquick mix and water until thoroughly moistened.
Spread batter in pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce carefully over batter.
Top with sausage mixture and remaining ingredients. Bake until crust is golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: light and fluffy cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth (not gritty).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust and chill.
Top with pie filling.

title: japanese fruitcake 1
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Alternate milk and sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla; beat until very smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Put 1/3 in one bowl and 2/3 in another.
To the 1/3 add cinnamon, cloves, allspice and 1/4 pound raisins.
Put batter into greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: green rice mold
directions: Combine pepper, onion and parsley with rice.
Mix milk and eggs and add to rice; add oil.
Pour into well-buttered ring mold. Place in pan of hot water; bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Invert and fill center with creamed shrimp or mushrooms.
Garnish with pimento, asparagus, peas, etc.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat. Add beans and taco mix. Spread in flat casserole. Spread with green taco sauce and sour cream. Top with grated cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with corn chips.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut the avocados open and scoop out all the meat.
Quickly sprinkle lemon juice over it to keep it from turning dark.
Add oil, sugar, salt, pepper, celery and mustard.
Mash avocado and blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves and sprinkle Tabasco sauce and chives over top.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add cocoa, flour and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rhubarb in bottom. Sprinkle jello over rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar and add marshmallows. Spread prepared cake mix on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
If frozen rhubarb is used, extend cooking time to 1 hour.
Happy eating.

title: krissie's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of the mushrooms; scrape and chop fairly fine. Wipe mushroom caps with a damp cloth.

title: tiny cheese cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together except eggs.
Add eggs; beat well.
Put wafers in cups (1 each).
Add filling, 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Top with fruit of your choice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together well
shape into a ball and roll into pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix together and add salt to taste and a small amount of vinegar and oil.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Add potatoes, ham, onions and green peppers; mix.
Bake in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 50 or 60 minutes.
Cover and bake another 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shrimp and snow peas hors d'oeuvres(eating well cookbook)
directions: Shrimp Directions:
String snow peas and place in pot of boiling, salted water.
Blanche for 45 seconds, counting from when water returns to boil.
Immediately remove from water with a slotted spoon and run under cold water.
Drain.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the first 2 ingredients in boiling salted water 5 minutes. Add the carrots. Drain and add the soup and sour cream. Combine the stuffing mix with the butter or margarine. Spread 1/2 of the stuffing on bottom of a 12 x 12 x 2-inch deep baking dish. Spread vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top of that and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: In medium bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat until mix is light and fluffy.
Beat in cream of tartar, then stir in flour and pecans.
Drop by heaping 1/2 teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven until rich golden, about 20 minutes.
These are small cookies and make approximately 5 dozen.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Warm soup in pan; add cheese, 1/4 cup or so at a time, until it is all melted.
Serve hot with chunks of French bread.

title: oat bran pancakes
directions: Heat nonstick griddle or frying pan over medium to medium high heat.

title: frankfort dump salad
directions: Dissolve the two packages of Jell-O in the hot water.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill in an 8 cup mold. Serves 12.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bell peppers. Stuff into peppers and wrap in foil. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift together dry ingredients. Alternately add cream, flour and bananas to butter mixture.
Add nuts; cool before slicing.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, soup, onion and celery.
In a baking dish, alternate layers of noodles and tuna mixture.
End layering with noodles on top (last) layer.
Season to taste.
Add water, a little at a time, if mixture is too dry.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties. Refrigerate until ready to fry.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: after school snack
directions: Spread peanut butter on one of the graham cracker squares. Add marshmallow on top.
Cook in microwave oven for 1/2 minute. Top with other graham cracker and press gently.
Cool for 1 minute.
Enjoy.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Remove from water; cool and remove meat from bones.
Cut chicken into small pieces; place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Layer half of onion, cheese and corn chips over chicken.
Combine soups and Ro-Tel.
Spoon half of soup mixture over casserole.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Score fat edge of ham and stud with cloves.
Place in 2 1/2-quart (13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) baking dish.
Combine citrus juices, honey and mustard and pour over ham.
Cover and bake.
When ready to serve, transfer ham to serving platter and keep warm.
Pour juice from baking dish into saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and water and stir into juice from ham.
Cook on medium heat until sauce thickens, boils and is clear and glossy.
Add raisins and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add orange pieces and serve hot over ham slice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, drain, set aside. (Use bit of oil in water to prevent sticky noodles.) Melt margarine in large pot, stir in flour, salt (if used), pepper and basil.
Stir until thick.
Add broth, stir well. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until thick.
Stir in chicken. Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese and egg. Spray 9X13 pan with cooking spray.
Place 1/3 of chicken mixture in bottom of pan.
Then 1/2 noodles.
Then 1/2 cottage cheese.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozarella.
Repeat layers, ending with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mom's recipe
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly for the best kitchen ever.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Break tortilla chips into pieces in a large bowl. Brown beef. Drain. Add to chips. Add dressing, cheese, onion, tomatoes, lettuce, beans and sprinkle 1/2 cup hot sauce.
Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers and serve cold later.

title: soupierior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in order listed. In large baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, two at a time, and beat.
Add flour and baking powder and mix good.
Add raisins, cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Mix and add lemon extract.
Bake in angel food pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour before opening oven, then test for doneness.
Keeps well.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Saute chopped onion and bell pepper in margarine. Strain out pepper and onion; set aside. Measure out 2 tablespoons of the margarine the onion and pepper were sauted in and put into a large frying pan. Heat margarine and add DRY Rice-A-Roni, cooking until light brown. Add 2 3/4 cups chicken broth and the flavor package which was included in the Rice-A-Roni. Add the chipped chicken, pepper, onions, sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Mix well, then heat, but do not boil. Pour mixture into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. During the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking, top casserole with Velveeta cheese.

title: country style ribs
directions: Place spare ribs in dutch oven.
Add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer covered for one hour or until ribs are tender.
Drain; place in 9x13 baking dish.
Heat oven to 300 degrees.
In medium skillet, saute onion in margarine. Stir in remaining ingredients, and cook until heated through. pour sauce over ribs.
Bake 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 5-6.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Melt butter with wine.
Saute onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic until tender.
Add shrimp and saute until cooked (approximately 5 minutes).
Add cheeses (cut Monterey into cubes), 1/2 quart whipping cream, parsley and seasoning.
Check to see if it is too thick.
If so, add more whipping cream.
Mixture should be fairly liquid, as the starch in the noodles will thicken it.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni al dente; rinse in cold running water.
Drain well.
Brown chuck lightly; drain and cool.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, grated cheese, chuck, shredded Mozzarella cheese and eggs.
Combine ziti with cheese mixture.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with spaghetti sauce.
Pour entire mixture of macaroni in dish.
Top with generous amount of sauce and additional grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix all ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Make a layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan with pretzels, butter or margarine, sugar and chopped nuts.
Beat cream cheese (softened) with powdered sugar 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread on first layer.

title: tropical orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water.
Drain pineapple and stir juice into gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and coconut.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Pour oil in bottom of 8-inch baking dish.
Add zucchini and Mozzarella cubes, salt and parsley.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Wash and remove seeds from chiles.
Pat dry.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half chiles, half cheeses and repeat, but save 1/2 cup cheese for topping.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix together all items, except the egg whites, then add beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: tater-dipped veggies
directions: In a small bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, celery salt, garlic powder and butter.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Dip vegetables, one at a time, into egg, then into potato mixture.
Coat well.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with dressing or dip, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Thaw hash browns just slightly.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or so until brown and bubbly.

title: sugarless fruit nut muffins
directions: Combine dates, raisins, prunes and water in pan; boil 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine; cool.
Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in muffin cups for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into two small greased loaf pans.
Bake in oven for one hour at 325°.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Before making cookies, write fortunes on strips of paper 1/2-inch wide and about 6 inches long.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add cooking oil and egg white.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add water and vanilla. Stir well.
Lightly grease skillet or griddle (Pam spray works well).
Make one cookie at a time by pouring 1 tablespoon of the batter in the skillet and spreading it into a 4-inch circle.
Cook over medium-low heat about 4 minutes or until lightly browned. Turn with wide pancake turner and cook 15 seconds more.
Working quickly, place cookie onto a pot holder.
While cookie is soft, put a fortune in the middle and fold cookie in half.
Bend the folded side over the edge of a bowl.
Gently pull the ends so the edges of cookie come together.
Put in a muffin pan to cool while keeping the shape.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup in large mixing bowl.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Add frosted rice cereal and mix until well coated.
Using back of spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly around side and in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill crust until set (approximately 15 minutes).
Spoon ice cream into pie crust. Add chocolate chips on top if desired.
Freeze until firm.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cake mix and pineapple juice.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back in middle.
When cool, add cream cheese, milk and vanilla instant pudding mixed together.
Put on top of cake.

title: potato salad(best when sits a day or overnight.)
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender.
Boil eggs until solid.
Dice the potatoes into large bowl.
Cut up eggs, onion and pickle in average-size pieces.
Mix with potatoes.
Add pickle juice, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Sprinkle paprika over all.
Add tomato wedges on top.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Will need 1 large cookie sheet or large pizza pan.

title: chili cheese popcorn
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in heavy 3-quart saucepan with lid.
Add popcorn.
Pop according to directions on popcorn container (7 to 8 cups of popped corn is needed.
If not enough, pop more).

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes; add 1/4 cup melted butter, egg yolks and salt.
Mix and divide into 20 portions. Wrap each portion around a marshmallow.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter to cornflake crumbs and rol leach portion in crumbs.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish and bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: creamy ham and macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
In large saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour, parsley flakes, dry mustard and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add cooked macaroni, ham, asparagus and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: white mountain pudding
directions: Mix gelatin with cold water.
Mix in boiling water.
Let stand until stiff.
Beat egg whites, sugar and lemon juice.
Add to gelatin and chill.
Boil milk, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Cook custard mixture over medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Serve. Put gelatin mixture into sherbet glasses and pour custard over mixture.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the crushed crackers and melted margarine; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party ham log
directions: Combine ham, cream cheese, green pepper, onion, pimiento, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in medium bowl.
Mix well to blend.
Spoon mixture onto waxed paper; mold into 2 logs about 3 to 4-inches long.
Wrap and chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
On waxed paper, combine chives with parsley. Roll chilled log in mixture, coating generously.
Arrange on serving plate and serve with crackers and sliced vegetables, if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream egg yolks and sugar in a saucepan.
Add half and half and vanilla.
Place over medium heat and stir until mixture thickens.
Take off heat and cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook chicken until done. Cut into small pieces. Cook pasta 10 minutes. Cool in cold water and drain well. Chop purple onion, celery and broccoli into small pieces. Drain English peas and combine all ingredients together. Add mayonnaise to taste. Refrigerate to marinate.

title: beef dip in bread
directions: With fingers pull out bite sized chunks of bread until about an inch shell of bread remains.
Fill with a mixture of the other ingredients and place bread chunks around outside for dipping.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon out onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: seafood vegetable spread
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; beat in sour cream and dip mix.
On serving plate, spread cheese mixture into a circle.
Chill at least one hour.
Just before serving, top with cocktail sauce, then crab meat.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Use a 12-inch round platter.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Boil rice for 13 minutes.
Melt butter in pan; add broccoli, celery and onion.
Cook for a few minutes.	Pour in soup and cheese and stir well.
Mix with rice and put in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ciaigie(angel wings)
directions: Beat liquid ingredients together.
Add baking powder.
Add flour and all dry ingredients to liquid.
Roll out and cut out squares.
Make a knot with square of dough.
Put in hot oil and fry.
Sprinkle after brown with powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; reserve 2 cups broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix broth and soup.
Bring to a boil and pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, pepper, flour and milk to form a batter.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May add Veg-All.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until set.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, onion, 1/2 of butter and cheese in a bowl.
Use a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spray it with Pam cooking spray. Pour thawed hash browns in dish.
Pour soup mixture over hash browns.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over mixture.
Pour remaining butter over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until mixture is bubbling and crackers are browned.

title: frijoles adriana de mexico(from argentina)
directions: Note:
A kilo is 2.2 pounds and queso doble crema is like Velveeta.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and water and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
May be eaten as is or iced with your favorite icing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients (except pecans) thoroughly and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: blender pancakes
directions: Put berries in blender first, then add everything else. Blend on high until smooth as you like it.
Heat griddle until you can drop a drop of water and it bounces across it.

title: soft peanut brittle
directions: Put peanuts in oven for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cook mixture and peanuts until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Add butter, powdered sugar and red food coloring to make pink.
Mix until it begins to stiffen.
Put on greased wax paper in drops.

title: jenny's apple short cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter to resemble size of peas.
Add only enough milk to resemble biscuit dough.
Spread dough with hands or fork into jelly roll pan; cover bottom evenly and up sides.
Cover with rows of apples; overlapping so all apples are covering dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake in 375 to 400 degree oven.
Watch carefully so edges don't burn - approximate time is 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, hard sauce *, or whipped topping.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat together sugar, zucchini and egg.
Add oil and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture and nuts. Pour batter in 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out and cool on rack.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugars, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and let cool.

title: haystacks
directions: In a double broiler, melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Mix noodles and nuts until coated well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Put into refrigerator until set.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt margarine; add onions, celery and parsley flakes. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together. Put into crock-pot on high for 45 minutes, then low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: creamy chocolate crescents
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt chocolate bars over low heat, stirring often.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in Cool Whip (mixture will thicken).
Cover and chill at least 1 to 2 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls or crescents.
Roll into crumbs. Chill thoroughly.
Makes about 66.

title: chilled hawaiian salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling pineapple juice. Cool.
Add vegetables and fruit.
Let stand until syrupy.
Fold in salad dressing.
Chill until firm.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add milk, butter and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cook at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and finish cooking (approximately 30 to 35 minutes).
If you use a deep dish pie crust, it will take longer to cook.

title: nutty snack mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a baking dish.
Pour butter evenly over mixture; stir to coat.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash vegetables.
Cut up all but tomatoes; add tomatoes whole. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.
Makes 10 to 15 cups.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Marinate chicken in Dales steak sauce.
Grill until chicken is done.
Place chicken into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with dressing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in lightly salted water until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Add peppers.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to make 1/3 cup liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in vegetables and pineapple.
Beat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork pizza loaf
directions: Brown ground pork.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt, seasoning, garlic salt and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Remove bread from inside of halved loaves.
Leave 1/2-inch shell.
Spread bread halves with pizza sauce, reserving 1/4 to 1/2 cup.
Place meat on bread and sauce; spread with reserved sauce.
Place onion, mushrooms and ground pepper in layers on top of meat.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Place on cookie sheet in oven; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add salt, sugar, cornstarch and 1 quart milk. Cook over double boiler until thickened.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Add the coffee cream and milk up to the fill mark.
Freeze.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown hamburger with the onion, salt and pepper to taste. Drain off most of fat.
Stir in flour and add milk.
Stir until thick.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green chilies on medium-high heat in a large Dutch oven pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes on low heat.
Serves 10.
This is a fast, easy recipe for a cold, wintery day.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until blended.
Add other ingredients and pour into square pan and refrigerate until set.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine all ingredients except for meat and mix well. Cut as much fat as possible from meat. Marinate the meat in the sauce for 24 hours in the refrigerator. Drain well and grill over open fire. Roll in corn or flour tortillas. Serve with sour cream, salsa, barbecue sauce, steak sauce or whatever you prefer.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle half of the graham cracker crumbs onto sides of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate, which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick. Stir in zucchini, pineapple, flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and walnuts.
Blend well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Mix dry pudding mix with apples, pineapple and oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese. Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with cheddar cheese and bake 35-40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil and flour three 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin all at once.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Pour into pans, filling each half full. Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick stuck in middle comes out clean.

title: charlie bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add brown sugar to shortening and beat well.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chips and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan.
Can be iced.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Moisten rice in melted butter mixed with sherry and some of the soups which have been blended together.
Put chicken pieces on top of rice mixture and onions on top of that.
Pour remaining soup over all.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and dust with paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°.

title: chippies
directions: Crush graham crackers in plastic Ziploc Baggie and then mix in bowl with Eagle Brand milk.
Add in chocolate chips.
Put in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Yields 10 to 20 bars, depending upon size.

title: halloween brew
directions: In a punch bowl, stir together the Eagle Brand and pineapple juice; add orange soda. Top with sherbet and serve over ice if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Mix all together except meat.
Place meat in large casserole and cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 5 to 6 hours. Stir occasionally to shred meat.
If necessary, remove lid for last 1/2 hour cooking time to reduce liquid.
Serve on buns.
This also does well in a slow cooker.

title: hot cranberry salad
directions: Oil a 2-quart casserole.
Place the chopped apples and cranberries in the casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cover with sugar.
In a medium mixing bowl, blend the oatmeal, walnuts, brown sugar and melted butter just to moisten.
Pour over fruit. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies("a quickie")
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and add the 3 liquid ingredients. Mix and form into balls. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes about 18 to 20 cookies.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: moms coffee cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and pour in a baking pan. Pour the topping mixture on top of the cake and bake at 350 until done.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble half of cookies in bottom of cake pan.
Pour melted stick of butter over cookies.
Mix cream cheese, 12 ounces whipped cream and 1 cup powdered sugar with mixer.
Pour over crumbs.
Mix package of chocolate pudding, Eagle Brand milk and 1 cup milk with mixer for 10 minutes or until thick.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Spread second 12 ounces of whipped cream on top of chocolate pudding layer and then crumble cookies on top.

title: sour cream chops
directions: Rub chops with sage, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet. Brown chops.
Add sliced onion and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove chops from skillet.
Combine sour cream and flour.
Add sour cream mixture to skillet.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over chops.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat the egg white.
Mix together the remaining ingredients except pecans and blend into the egg white.
Mix pecans into the spice and egg white mixture.
Put in pan, spreading them out. Bake in oven for 35 minutes at 325° and stir every 10 minutes.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan; cover with water.
Cook until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix jello, Kool-Aid, sugar and hot water first. Then when it's well mixed, add the cold water and mix. Pour in popsicle containers and freeze.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk, stirring constantly.
Pour immediately into lime jello to dissolve.
Add cream cheese to dissolve, then add pineapple and mayonnaise.
Add whipped cream, blending well. Pour into a dish (3-quart) and refrigerate.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli per directions and drain.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, onions and soup.
Blend well.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Pour in greased casserole and bake at 325° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: baked yellowtail snapper with balsamic vinegar(3 to 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a small knife, make 2 diagonal slices about 1/2 inch deep on both sides of fish.
Dust fish with flour and shake off any excess.

title: master mix
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Stir dry milk solids, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into flour.
Sift together 3 times into a large mixing bowl and cut in shortening until master mix is the consistency of cornmeal.
Store in covered containers at room temperature until used in recipe.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with assorted fresh fruit.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Coat bottom of pot with olive oil.
Saute chopped meat and drain fat.
Saute onion and mix with meat.
Add tomato paste, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Fill pot 3/4 full of water.
Add chicken to cook on medium flame and cook for 2 hours or until chicken is ready.
Add salt and pepper.
Boil rice when ready to remove chicken from gravy and add rice to it.
Let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Feeds 6 to 8 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Cut up in small pieces.
Combine all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Put cracker crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Mix in seasoning mix.
In rectangle pan, place a layer of meat in bottom of pan.
Spread 1 can of beans over meat.
Spread sour cream over beans.
Mix both cheeses and sprinkle over top, then top with tomatoes and rest of cheese.
Use lettuce as option.
Bake in oven just until cheese melts.
Serve with chips.

title: anne's sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together sweet potatoes, vanilla, melted butter, sugar, eggs and milk.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13 inch or 9 x 9 inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour and butter for topping until crumbly, using processor fitted with steel knife, or pastry blender.
Mix in nuts. Sprinkle topping mixture over sweet potatoes.
At this point, dish can be refrigerated, covered.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until browned and bubbly.

title: wrapped cocktail wieners
directions: Mix wieners with barbecue sauce.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Drain wieners.
Separate rolls into triangles, then cut in half.
Wrap triangles around each wiener.
Bake as directed on package of crescent rolls.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim any fat and bone from meat.
Cut into 4 to 6 serving size pieces.
Grease skillet lightly with fat from meat.
Brown meat thoroughly on one side; turn.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Brown other side of meat; turn.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Push meat to side of skillet.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender.
Add bouillon, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers; cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Freeze.

title: sour cream date drops
directions: Cut dates and chop nuts coarsely.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and beat well.
Blend in sour cream and orange rind.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soup and cheese.
Put in a shallow casserole or cake pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the casserole and then sprinkle the melted butter or margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and corn tortillas.
Add chicken broth until you have a smooth consistency.
Put remainder of chicken broth on to heat to a boil.
You saute corn tortillas in the chicken broth for about 10 seconds individually as you use them.
You then layer mixture with corn tortillas.
You have about 3 to 4 layers in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover the top with the grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Slowly add flour, soda, powder and salt.
Mix all together and chill overnight.
Dust board with flour and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with round cutter and lay aside.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 quarts boiling water and 1 teaspoon salt. Blanch peppers 3 to 5 minutes after removing seeds.
Combine meat and soup, etc.
Fill the peppers with mixture and replace cap of the pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top each pepper with a little of the soup and bake 10 minutes or until tender.
Use only 1 cup of the soup in the pepper filling mixture.
Save the rest for the final 10 minutes of the baking.

title: salmon party roll
directions: Drain salmon; flake with a fork.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and liquid smoke; stir well.
Chill mixture several hours or overnight.
Shape salmon mixture into a log.
Combine pecans and parsley.

title: florida-cracker key lime pie
directions: Beat 1 whole egg.
Add condensed milk, lime juice and egg yolks (reserving egg whites).
Stir with spoon by hand until mixture is a smooth and creamy texture.
Add pinch of salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over lime pie filling.
Bake in slow 350° oven until meringue is light brown (12 to 15 minutes).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and dry dressing together.
Add to the salad and toss.
Chill and serve.

title: dumpling
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough out to about 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 1-inch strips or squares.
Drop into chicken stock.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cooked broccoli, cheese and soup; stir until cheese is melted.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbling.
To reduce fat, use only 1/2 stick margarine and lite Cheez Whiz.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: hash, monday
directions: Mix ingredients; press gently into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until vegetables are tender.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in eggs and oil until dry ingredients are moist. Add vanilla, pineapple with juice, pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove and cool.
Frost.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: almond-coconut topping
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in brown sugar and vanilla; mix together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in coconut and almonds or other nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until topping is golden brown. Cool slightly, then cut into bars.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
All bread to rise 10 minutes before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: escalloped corn and tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, corn, eggs, flour, sugar and pepper.
Turn into 17 x 7 1/2 x 2 inch baking dish.
Melt butter, add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan; add to butter mixture and toss to combine.
Sprinkle over baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, except onion and green pepper.
Cook on medium heat until thick and bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in onion and green pepper.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: noodle bean casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until done; set aside.
