Drain green beans. Add mushroom soup.
Add to noodles.
Mix in onion or onion soup and salt and pepper.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water in saucepan over low heat 10 to 15 minutes until raisins are plump.
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Cream the shortening and sugar with mixer in medium bowl.
Add egg and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Stir in cooled raisin liquid.
Continue to beat until fluffy.
Blend dry ingredients together with spices. Blend into creamed mixture.
Add oats, raisins and nuts and mix it by hand.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken noodle
directions: Boil chicken breast. Set aside when done.
Boil wide noodles according to package.
Drain noodles; mix chicken and 2 cans of soup.
Mix well and heat until hot. Salt and pepper to taste, then ready to serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Set oven at 350°.
In medium pan, melt margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring to a rolling boil. Set aside for a few minutes.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
In a small bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat egg mixture into flour mixture and then add that to the cocoa mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together.
Spread atop pineapple.
Crush crackers and spread atop cheese mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar. Stir together water and yeast. Stir eggs into Crisco and sugar. Stir in yeast and water. Mix flour and salt. Stir in flour about 1/2 cup at a time. Will be real sticky. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator. Will double in bulk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, raisins, onions and sunflower seeds. For dressing, mix together mayonnaise, red wine vinegar and brown sugar.
Mix dressing with salad ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate cake(over 100 years old)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a cup or bowl and let stand.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, shortening and egg yolks.
Add chocolate mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sicilian sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage in a large saucepan, breaking up meat with wooden spoon, until meat loses its pink color.
(If using Italian sausage, remove casings before cooking.)
Add onion; saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, broth and basil; bring to boiling. Stir in orzo, salt and pepper.
Lower heat; cover and simmer until orzo is tender, about 10 minutes.
Taste and add additional salt and pepper, if needed.
Ladle into a tureen or soup bowls.
Serve with bread sticks or sesame crackers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spicy zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini and
boiling
water
in large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat
at
low
speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Spoon
into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: chocolate thumbprints(1993 brownie bake-off winner)
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; cool.
Cream the margarine. Add melted chocolate.
Add sugar, egg yolk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Sift flour and salt; add to mixture.
Slightly beat egg white with fork.
Roll dough into balls (about 1 teaspoon per ball).
Dip in egg white to coat.
Roll in nuts.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint in each gently.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out immediately. Place 3 to 4 chocolate chips in thumbprint.
When melted, spread evenly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy cheese torte
directions: Butter spring-form and dust sides and bottom with crumbs.
In a mixer, cream cottage cheese and then add rest of ingredients one at a time, until all are gone.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand in oven with door closed for 2 hours. Refrigerate.

title: easy fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan; set aside.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Use foil to lift fudge out of pan; place on cutting board.
Peel off foil; cut into pieces. Store tightly covered in cool, dry place.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large casserole dish, break one head lettuce.
Chop the celery and bell pepper.
Pour over lettuce.
Layer drained, sliced water chestnuts and drained peas.
Spread top with Miracle Whip. Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Dump diced bread in a large crock-pot.
(If prefer a less moist dressing, spread cut up bread pieces out to dry while preparing remaining ingredients.)
Saute sausage.
When meat is partially cooked, add celery and onion.
When they are almost transparent, add mushrooms and cook until they are just done. Toss meat mixture with the bread in the pot.
Mix together liquids, eggs and seasonings; add to the bread along with the apricots. Toss all gently but thoroughly.
Set pot on high for 1 hour. Decrease to low and cook at least 4 hours.
More time can't hurt it.
Remember, no peaky!

title: all-purpose cookies
directions: This batter can be formed into a roll and chilled, then sliced for refrigerator cookies, or rolled into balls and flattened for decorative cookies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
By adding nuts, fruits, chips, etc. or substituting ingredients, this recipe will make an endless variety of cookies.

title: grilled teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well and baste chicken with sauce.

title: pork roast with sauerkraut
directions: Place roast in covered roasting dish or pan*.
Top with sauerkraut, including juice.
Roast at 200° for 8 to 9 hours.
Do not open oven or uncover.
Tastes good with mashed or boiled potatoes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add milk alternately with flour that has been sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add lemon rind.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 60 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 minutes.

title: nacho bean dip
directions: Combine beans, butter, 2 ounces cheese, chilies, half the onion, cumin and chili powder. Heat thoroughly. Put chips on ovensafe plate. Spoon bean mixture on top of chips, then add cheese evenly. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Garnish with remaining onions.

title: stay a bed stew
directions: Mix and place all in a baking dish with tight cover.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Add egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in walnut sized balls.
Dip in cold water and roll in granulated sugar.
This gives a professional finish to top of cookie and tastes good.
Place in lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cantaloupe salad
directions: Cut six rings about 1/2 in. wide from the center section of the cantaloupe.
Remove seeds and set rings aside.
Cube the remaining cantaloupe into a bowl, combine orange juice and honey. Add grapes, kiwi and cubed cantaloupe rings on lettuce.
Top with fruit and sprinkle with coconut.
Yields: 6 servings

title: macaroni with two cheeses
directions: Heat oil in saucepan. Add garlic, onion and carrot. Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in sauce, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling. Simmer 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Combine cheese and pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour and juice. Stir into pineapple and cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Mix crackers and margarine; put over dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This recipe goes good with ham.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Combine milk and ice cream in bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat slowly with mixer just until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour immediately into pie crust.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices; salt and let set about 30 minutes.
Drain off brown juice.
Mix meal and flour, then roll eggplant in mixture.
Brown eggplant in shortening. Then saute onion.
Fry ground chuck and drain.
Layer in buttered casserole:
1st layer eggplant, 2nd layer onion, 3rd layer ground chuck and 4th layer sliced tomatoes.
Make 2 or 3 layers, according to size of casserole you want.
Cover top well with buttered cracker crumbs.
Cover well with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bill's meat and pickle salad]
directions: In an old-fashioned table meat grinder, grind bologna and pickles into a casserole dish.
Mix with Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.
Tastes great on homemade bread.
Kids love it.

title: ray's quick milkshake
directions: In blender container, combine ice cream and milk. Cover and blend just until mixed.
Makes 4 (5 ounce) servings or one big shake.

title: coconut tarts
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 20 minutes.
Slowly add coconut and margarine.
Let cool.
Add eggs.
Put into 16 unbaked tart shells.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Sift first four ingredients.
Stir in egg, butter, milk, sour cream and vanilla until just moistened.
Gently fold in berries.
Fill paper lined muffin tins and bake about 20 minutes.
Makes 12.
Awesome snack warm from the oven with butter!

title: vegetable soup with beef
directions: Toss beef with flour, salt and pepper.
In a large Dutch oven, brown the meat in batches in oil; drain.
Transfer to a large stockpot or soup kettle.
Add garlic, bay leaves, thyme, water, tomato sauce and juice, bouillon and barley.
Bring to a boil.

title: pie crust cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add flour and cinnamon, then unbeaten egg yolk.
Use a lightly buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch cookie sheet.
Put the lump of dough in the center of the cookie sheet and spread with hands, patting and pressing until the entire pan is covered evenly.
Beat egg white slightly and spread over top of dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 275°. After baking, cool 1 minute, then cut strips down and vertically across, making diamond shaped cookies.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add alternately the milk with vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Add chocolate syrup last.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or longer.
Start in cold oven.

title: gladys' cherry easy dessert(freda e. quintero's mom)
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Pat in pan (oblong 12 x 9-inch pan). Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown the meat with onion and Italian seasoning.
Drain.
Boil the noodles until tender, with the potato and celery.
Pour this in with the meat in a large pan and add all other ingredients. You may need to add more Italian seasoning.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Melt and simmer butter, onion and celery.
Mix soup and water. Pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 box frozen chopped broccoli.
Mix all together with broccoli; add 1 1/2 cups Minute rice.
Dab a small jar Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Stir and bake 20 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Braise chicken on both sides.
Place in layers in deep dish chicken, then pepper and onion, over and over until full to top. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to soup and pour over chicken.
Add thyme.
Do not stir.
Place in oven and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (test for doneness before adding cheese).
Add cheese the last 10 minutes to melt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until syrup forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Take from stove and add soda and butter. Pour over popped corn and form into balls.
Use quite a good sized pan because when you add the soda, you will need the dishpan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Arrange biscuits in dish.
Dip each in melted butter and turn over before placing next biscuit. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Mix powdered sugar and water.
Drizzle over rolls.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat eggs in pan; put in cheese, dry mustard, milk and salt and pepper.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Cook macaroni; drain and put in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over the macaroni.
Put some bread crumbs and dabs of butter on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flour.
Add cream and mix well. Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
(May use less shortening in shell.)
Bake in 325° oven very slow.
It will thicken as it browns.
Makes a yellow filling and a brown top. Yields 2 medium size pies or 1 very large one.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Combine flours, oats, cornmeal, liver powder, salt and garlic powder in large bowl.
Add egg, oil and broth; mix well.
Dough should be soft but firm enough to roll.
Add more flour or broth as necessary to make the desired consistency.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut with bone or heart shaped cookie cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on foil lined baking sheet.
Prick line of dots down center of biscuits with toothpick and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn off oven.
Let stand in closed oven overnight. Store in plastic bag for up to 3 months.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mash potatoes. Combine them with eggs, butter, milk, sugars and flavorings. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with Pecan Topping.

title: family soup
directions: In a large pot, cover beef and bones with water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add onion and celery.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Remove beef and bones.
Discard bones.
Set aside beef.
Strain broth into bowl and chill to congeal fat.
Lift off fat and discard.
Return broth to pot.
Cut beef into bite size pieces and add to pot.
Add barley and simmer for 1 hour.
Add remainder of ingredients except salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: uncle bob's gumbo
directions: Brown flour in grease; simmer for 30 minutes until browned. Saute vegetables; set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to flour mixture; simmer for 1 hour.
Add shrimp and vegetables.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients except strawberry preserves.
Spray ring mold with Pam. Place in mold and refrigerate until firm.
Fill center with preserves and serve with crackers.

title: almonds in honey
directions: On a small baking sheet, toast almonds in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, stirring once or twice until golden.
Cool on a wire rack.
Place almonds in a clean 1 pint jar.
Add honey slowly, using a table knife or narrow spatula to help honey drizzle down through the almonds.
Cover.
Store in a cool, dry place for 1 month.
Spoon over ice cream or yogurt.
Freeze for longer storage.
Makes 1 pint of topping.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Brown chopped onion in pan with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Pour in pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup and water.
Stir and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour slowly, about 2 cups, with electric mixer.
Work the rest in with hands.
Add only as much flour as butter will absorb.
When dough no longer sticks to bowl, enough flour has been added.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: Blend cookies in food processor until crumbly (or beat with a hammer).
Transfer to bowl and crush large pieces; set aside.
In large bowl combine margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix milk and pudding together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put top of Cool Whip cover in the bottom of an 8-inch flowerpot. Layer each beginning with 1 layer of crumbs and 1 layer of cream. Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with a shovel.

title: baked chicken and noodles
directions: Combine soup and milk until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in greased 1-quart dish. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: corn
directions: Stir together and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with shredded cheddar cheese.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: chocolate angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Cook pudding mix according to package; pour over cake pieces.
Use a fork or spoon to move cake around so filling gets between.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water until tender.
Drain and save liquid. Add water to liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add liquid and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add gradually to shortening and liquid mixture. Mix well.
Add oats.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet that has been greased and floured lightly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Beat well and bake in 3 layers at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin spice and salt in large bowl; pour into 9x13 baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans and drizzle with melted butter.

title: sweetbread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Melt butter in milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add to first mixture.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add flour and knead well about 1/2 hour.
Let raise until double in bulk, punch down and let raise again.
Brush top with milk after shaping into two loaves.
Bake at 325° for one hour or more.

title: apple squares
directions: Put apples in a saucepan with sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the consistency of chunky applesauce. Cool to room temperature.
Makes two cups.

title: saltine cookies
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Line pan with foil and spray with Pam.
Put crackers in a layer on foil.
Pour butter and brown sugar mixture over crackers.
Spread chocolate chips on top while hot.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes. Break apart.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, baking soda, allspice, cinnamon and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Stir in pears and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand until cool. Remove and dust with powdered sugar.

title: margie's crock-pot beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in the crock-pot and cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: marinated artichoke dip
directions: Spread artichokes in a pie plate or shallow casserole; spread mayonnaise over.
Sprinkle with green chiles and top with cheese. Heat in microwave until cheese melts; serve with tortilla chips.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix to dissolve Jell-O and water.
Add other ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter and vanilla to hot milk.
Mix with egg mixture.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chess pie (egg)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; cream well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Reduce speed to slow; add milk and seasonings.
Place in a baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Then, reduce heat to 300°; cook for 30 more minutes.

title: christmas scones
directions: Combine flour sugar, orange peel and baking soda. Cut in butter until resembles crumbs. Add cranberries. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Form dough into 2 equal balls. On floured surface work ball into 6 inch circle 1/2 inch thick. Cut circle into 6 wedges. Place on nonstick baking sheet, leaving 1 inch between each one. Repeat using remaining dough. Bake until lightly brown, about 10-15 minutes. Serve with whipped cream and orange marmalade. Makes 12 servings

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together; place on bottom of spring pan and bake at 400° approximately 8 minutes.

title: face paint
directions: In each muffin cup mix the cornstarch, water, cold cream and food coloring, a different color for each cup.
Store.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in egg.
Mix and sift together flour and salt and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, to which the soda has been added.
Stir in molasses.
Add the blueberries, stirring carefully to mix.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 7 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 4 tablespoons sugar evenly over the batter.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes or until done.
The sugar sprinkled over the batter makes a crusty topping on the cake when it is baked.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: english toffee christmas candy
directions: In an iron skillet, mix the sugar, butter and salt together. Bring to a boil and boil to a hard crack stage (300° on a candy thermometer).
Stir constantly so it won't burn.
When hard crack stage is reached, pour toffee onto cookie sheets.
In the winter place outside until it hardens.
Bring in and pour melted chocolate over.
When chocolate is set, break toffee into serving pieces.
Store in tightly covered tin.

title: deviled cream sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients except the vegetables with the cup of milk.
Cook, stirring until cooked and thickened. Stir small amounts of hot mix into the sour cream.
Mix all together.
Pour over hot cooked vegetables.
Heat more if necessary, but, do not boil.

title: vanilla cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time and beat. Crumble vanilla wafers into mixture; add coconut and nuts. Fold together. Pour in greased tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Mix all liquids and sugar in a large pot.
Wrap spices in cheesecloth and add to liquid.
Simmer 1 hour on stove top.
Remove spices before serving.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix and cook until thick enough to spread on cake layers.

title: spinach salad 2
directions: Fry, drain and crumble bacon.
Wash, dry and tear up spinach. Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts and several chopped, hard-boiled eggs.
Mix together with bacon and add dressing.

title: every good cook's vegetable stock
directions: Place oil in a deep pot.
Add the onion, leek, carrot and fennel.
Toss and cover tightly.
Cook over very low heat for about 5 minutes, shaking pan occasionally so as not to let vegetables scorch.
Add celery, tomato and cabbage; toss again.
Cover tightly; continue to cook over very low heat for an additional 10 minutes, shaking pan occasionally.
Add water and bay leaf.
Bring to a simmer and cook, barely simmering, for 30 minutes, skimming as necessary.
Put ingredients through a strainer which has been lined with a double thickness of damp cheesecloth.
Allow to cool and refrigerate, sealed or freeze.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: koop's broiled mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; break out stems and dip mushrooms in melted butter.
Place on pan - cap side up.
Put about 1/2 tsp. butter in cap and sprinkle with garlic powder and about 1 tsp. sherry.
Add enough bread crumbs to absorb butter and sherry.

title: creamy broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Add broccoli, soup and slightly beaten egg yolks.
Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into rice mixture. Empty mixture into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: fry bread
directions: Add water to form dough.
Knead until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Cover with a cloth and let stand for about 2 hours. Shape into 2-inch balls.
Flatten by patting with hands until a circle about 8-inches in diameter is formed.
Or use a rolling pin.

title: melon and prosciutto
directions: Cut cantaloupe or honeydew melon in half and remove seeds. Use a melon baller to scoop out pulp, or cut pulp into bite-size cubes.
Cut Prosciutto or ham into 1-inch wide strips.
Wrap 1 strip of Prosciutto or ham around each melon ball.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Makes about 36.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with sugar and salt.

title: a christmas salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix chopped apple in and put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: brownie bottom cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and chocolate in large saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add sugar and eggs until blended.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt, mixing just until blended.
Spread evenly into greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
While Brownie Bottom is baking, prepare Cheesecake.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger until done.
Add onion and bell pepper and cook until tender; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook rice and add to the other mixture.

title: cheese paska
directions: Blend together well cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Add softened butter and cream together.
Add sugar gradually and mix until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Mix well.
Fold in vanilla, raisins and almonds.
Place in cheesecloth and put in mold (clay flowerpot and special mold, if you have one).
Cover well and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Remove from mold and decorate with cherries.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl; pour in pie shell or baking bowl.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour, covered with plastic wrap.
Cream together the butter and sugars. Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda to sugar mixture.
Mix well. Blend in the egg-raisin mixture, oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Dough will be stiff.

title: e-z peanut butter cookies
directions: Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry custard pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine 2/3 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons cornstarch and salt; stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook stirring constantly, 1 minute.
(Let mixture come to a boil slowly; when cooking after boiling has begun, it will begin to thicken.)

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add liquid ingredients. Add nuts and coconut last, stirring in by hand. Grease and flour 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow covered casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over a bed of egg noodles or rice.

title: yum yum steak
directions: Salt,
pepper
and
paprika steak on both sides.
Place thin slices
of	garlic	all over steak.
Bake uncovered in a foil lined pan at 350° for about 45 minutes, turning once.

title: fresh corn oysters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Combine egg, corn, whipping cream and butter.
Mix well and stir in dry ingredients.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into hot oil (375°).
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: freda's apple pie
directions: In pie crust, slice apples, fill up pie crust.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and pour mixture over apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter.
Press into a 12 x 16-inch glass pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour into pan.
Let set 5 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to eat. Yields approximately 8 servings.

title: pork tenderloin in wine sauce
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch slices.
Shake with mixture of flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper in plastic bag, coating well.
Add pork and shallot to heated butter in skillet.
Cook for 4 minutes or until brown on 1 side; turn pork.
Add mushrooms and rosemary. Cook for 1 minute or until mushrooms are tender.
Add mixture of wine and chicken broth.
Cook for 3 minutes or until pork is tender.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine evaporated milk and chocolate pieces in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until chocolate is melted.
Serve hot.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples until they are like applesauce. Add sugar and cinnamon to taste. Take canned biscuits and roll flat in flour into a circle. Place about 2 or 3 tablespoons of apple mixture in the center of each. Fold over and press sides together with a fork. Place in hot oil and fry until brown on both sides. Remove and drain on paper towel.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until pie crust edge is golden brown.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with cottage cheese, sour cream, vanilla, butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan with butter; pour batter in pan.
Sprinkle with more cinnamon and dab corners with a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: top o' the stove scallop
directions: Put in heavy skillet the potatoes and ham.
Add soup, water, onions, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat, turning now and then for about 25 minutes.
Remove cover and cook 10 minutes longer, then pour 1/2 cup evaporated milk over the top.
Heat until steaming hot, but do not boil.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients except nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in a tube pan that has been greased.
Set a small ovenproof container of water in oven during baking for moisture.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie filling; set aside to chill in serving dish.
After the jello has chilled, combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla; spread this topping over the chilled jello mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the topping.

title: hot and spicy shrimp
directions: Saute garlic in
butter
for
10 to 15 minutes over low heat. Mix remaining ingredients, except shrimp, add to butter and garlic; simmer gently for 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Allow to cool
completely
and pour over shrimp in a casserole dish with lid.
All
shrimp
should
be submerged in marinade. Marinate 2 to 3
hours
or
up to 3 to 4 days in refrigerator. Place open casserole
in
400° oven for 10 minutes, remove and stir thoroughly.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Shrimp will continue to cook,
even
when
removed
from oven.
Serve with French bread for dipping.
Serves 4 as appetizers.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Heat water to boiling; add ground beef, chopped onion and soup mix.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Add vegetables, tomato sauce, tomatoes and orzo.
Bring to boil again; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Let stand awhile before serving for flavors to blend.

title: egg foo yong(paper)
directions: Brown chicken lightly in butter and add bean sprouts, onion, celery and green pepper.
Cover and cook until onion is transparent. Cool slightly.
Spoon chicken into beaten eggs, straining them free of liquid.
Add salt. Mix thoroughly.
Pour 1/2 cup of mixture into hot fat about 1/2-inch deep.
Flatten each cake to 1/2-inch thickness and cook until nicely browned on both sides, turning once.
Drain and serve while hot with sauce.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: brazil nut speedies
directions: Blend milk with cocoa thoroughly. Stir in chopped nuts and mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Pat pineapple dry; soften cream cheese, then mix all ingredients.
If using nuts, put some inside and then roll the cheese ball in remaining nuts.
Chill before serving.
Best to chill overnight so flavors can mix.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple slightly.
In medium bowl, combine pineapple, pudding, Cool Whip, marshmallows and walnuts.
Mix until all are well blended.
Green food coloring may be added to enhance the color.
May be served immediately or placed in refrigerator.

title: cream caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Alternating, add flour and sour cream to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three 9-inch prepared pans. Bake for 25 - 35 minutes.
Test doneness.
Remove from oven and cool on racks for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove from pans to cool completely.
Frost.

title: caesar salad(eating light)
directions: Combine bread cubes and 2 cloves crushed garlic in large zip-top plastic bag.
Seal bag; shake to coat bread cubes.
Turn bread cube mixture onto a baking sheet.
Arrange bread cubes in a single layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toasted.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture until it resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins or pieces of dried fruit.
Mix milk and cider vinegar and gradually add dry ingredients, mixing lightly, until dough masses together to form a ball.
Dough will be soft.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture; mix well.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove cake from pan.

title: black-eyed peas supper dish
directions: Scramble sausage in frying pan until done; drain.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring vegetables into sausage.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Stir well.
Pour in peas with liquid from can.
Cover and simmer slowly 15 minutes. Serve very hot with grated cheese sprinkled on top.
If prepared ahead of time, the flavors have better chance to blend.
Reheat at mealtime and top with cheese when ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour in mold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Cook beef in large skillet with onion until browned slightly; put macaroni in saucepan of boiling water.
Cook only until swelled; drain, but not completely.
Combine all ingredients. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is of desired taste. Serves 6.

title: chop suey or chow mein for 2lubbock, texas
directions: Use wok or skillet to heat oil over medium heat.
Cook meat with garlic until browned.
Add all vegetables and seasonings and 1/2 c. water.
Stir, cover and bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and continue stirring until thick and smooth. Cover for 2 minutes and serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: salmon stew
directions: Bring soups milk, and celery salt to boil-add salmon and margarine.
Bring just to boiling point.
Turn stove off and serve.
Very good.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, strawberries and Cool Whip. Pour over angel food cake. Mix gently. Refrigerate.

title: smuckers
directions: Roll dough thin.
Sprinkle sugar and spices liberally.
Add small dots of butter over dough.
Drop vanilla over dough.
Roll pastry up like a jelly roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until dough is slightly browned.
Cut into slices.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and do not peel; slice into 1/4-inch slices. Cook in boiling water until done.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease long Pyrex casserole.
Layer potatoes, cheese and bacon.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter over.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with sprinkles of parsley and paprika.
Bake for about 15 minutes.

title: charlotte's soup
directions: Stew beef and cover with water.
Simmer.
Add vegetables and soup.
Make rice and barley according to directions on box.
Add to soup.
Season to taste.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt cheese; add salsa, blending well.
Serve hot with a variety of chips.

title: unusual potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, corn meal, flour, onions, salt and pepper in Ziploc bag. Shake for 3 to 5 minutes. Place in frying pan with 1-inch cooking oil. Cook until done.

title: clam blobs
directions: Mix everything together but the toast rounds and refrigerate if you wish.
Pile mixture on toast and stick under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Season	oysters
with
salt and pepper.
Wrap each in a slice of	bacon.	Fasten	with
toothpicks.
Fry	in hot fat. Serve on buttered toast.

title: charleene's witches brew
directions: Mix thoroughly; refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Serve over ice.
(Better the longer it stands.)

title: grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Add grapes. Stir and set aside. Mix brown sugar and pecans. Pour on top of grape mixture. Chill.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onions in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Bring water to a boil.
Cook noodles.
Cube cheese and melt with 2 cups milk.
Add remaining milk.
Combine milk mixture, broccoli, and onions with the noodles.
Season to taste with garlic powder.
To thin, add extra milk or water.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add all other ingredients. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of the nuts. Dot with oleo sliced thin on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crescent cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook meat over medium-high heat until it is thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Make the sloppy joes according to the package directions.
Meanwhile, separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles. Place triangles in ungreased 9 inch glass pie pan or 8-1/4 inch round glass baking dish; press over bottom and up sides to form the crust.
Sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese.
Top with cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: black bottom goodies
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well at the center of the mixture.
Combine the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla, mixing well.
Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Combine the cream cheese and next three ingredients, stirring well.
Stir in the chocolate morsels.
Spoon about one teaspoon of the cream cheese mixture over the chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes five dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in medium oven (350°) for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix
first
7 ingredients, heat in saucepan until sugar has dissolved.
Cream 1 1/4 cups sugar and butter;
add flour and milk.
Blend
well.
Pour
in
shallow
baking
dish, 9 x 13-inch. Spread evenly over bottom;
pour cherry mixture over top. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put broccoli, chicken bouillon, onion and salt in 2 quarts of water; cook until tender.
A crock-pot works very well.
Make a white sauce.
Melt butter; stir in flour and add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add in cream cheese (cut up in small chunks); stir until melted, then add broccoli.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: frog eye salad(acini de pepe fruit salad)
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to boil.
Add acini de pepe.
Cook at rolling boil until macaroni is done.
Drain; rinse with water.
Drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture with macaroni.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate until chilled. Serves 25.

title: tomato cake
directions: Beat eggs, light; add tomatoes, melted shortening, pepper and salt.
Stir in cracker crumbs to make it stiff enough to drop by tablespoonfuls on a hot griddle or frying pan.
Brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Can roll in nuts or use as spread in a bowl.

title: beef tips
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over meat, coating each piece thoroughly.
Brown quickly in hot oil.
Place meat in baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion, vinegar, water and seasoning.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hurricane cocktails
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a tall pitcher or large pot and stir to dissolve the sugar.
Pour into a punch bowl and add the ice cubes and orange segments.
Serve in tall glasses over the rocks with straws.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break up bread in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Add milk to eggs to make 1 1/2 cups and add dry mustard to egg mixture. Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (may add more than 4 ounces if you wish).
Sprinkle with sausage (fried and drained). Let set overnight (in refrigerator).
Before baking the next morning, add cream of mushroom soup, mixed with 1/2 cup milk (may use skim).
Just pour soup mixture over bread and egg mixture. Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fudgy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oats and pecans in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar and cocoa in a medium saucepan.
Add milk, mixing well.
Add butter.
Place over high heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: glazed pork chops with maple syrup
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pat pork chops dry.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Dredge pork chops in flour, shaking off excess.
Add to skillet and cook until brown, about 4 minutes per side.
Transfer to roasting pan (do not wash skillet).
Bake pork chops until thermometer inserted in thickest part registers 145° (about 20 minutes).

title: carrot relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This will keep for a good while in the refrigerator.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix and jello.
Add oil and eggs.
Roll into balls and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Longer baking time for crunchy cookies.)

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan. Bake in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve cold.

title: people chow
directions: Melt together in double boiler margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips until smooth and creamy.
In large bowl combine chocolate mixture and large box of Crispix cereal.
Stir to coat well in brown bag.
Mix confectioners sugar, add coated cereal and shake well.
Spread on wax paper to dry.

title: orange-banana pops
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well at low speed of an electric mixer.
Pour evenly into six 5 ounce paper cups. Partially freeze; insert a wooden stick into center of each cup and freeze until firm.
When ready to serve, let pops stand at room temperature 5 minutes; peel away cups.
A serving amount is 1 cup at 77 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 fruit.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and cool.
Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Mix all together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: beef noodles
directions: Fry ground meat, dice onion and pepper.
Fry with meat.
Add butter.
Boil noodles, start soup in pan.
When ground meat is done, add to mushroom soup and mix.
Add noodles, salt and pepper to taste, heat and serve.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash until tender;
mash and drain.
Add remaining ingredients
except
corn meal.
Add more bread crumbs if mixture is too soft to handle.
Shape mixture into croquettes; roll
in corn meal and deep fry until golden brown.	Yields 6 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Marinate for 3 or 4 days.
Dry in a food dehydrator.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix bread and pineapple together; put in casserole.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, pineapple juice and butter.
Beat and pour over pineapple and bread. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 or 3 layers according to package directions.
Cool and frost with Cool Whip Frosting.
